title: frozen lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks, sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped topping.
Freeze 4 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Freeze leftovers.
Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, prunes and nuts.
Bake in buttered and floured pan for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: trail mix cookies
directions: Beat sugars, margarine and shortening in large bowl with a wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix in oats, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in flour, oat bran, wheat germ, baking powder and baking soda thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Stir in candies, peanuts and raisins.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes or just until cookies are set and begin to brown.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pastry.
Lattice work over top.
Bake at 325° about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add rice, chili powder, tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir together and pour in ungreased casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover dish while baking.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together until creamy and put aside.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Use blender or mixer to blend or beat all together.
Pour into greased large pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Spread the cherry pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the pie filling and pour 1 1/2 sticks of melted margarine evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked mahi-mahi
directions: Soak the fish in a Ziploc bag of milk overnight. Drain the fish. Rinse and pat dry. Place skin side down in an oiled baking dish. Combine the remaining ingredients. Apply the mustard bread crumb mixture to fillets. Bake at 350° until fish is done (approximately 20 minutes).

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Roll in 1 cup chopped dried beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole mix all ingredients except Cheez Whiz. Once mixed, drop Cheez Whiz by spoonfuls on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
As cheese melts, mix in.
Can also be baked in microwave.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti per package directions.
Rinse with cold water. Mix all ingredients.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Garnish and serve.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Place croutons in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown sausage.
Drain and crumble.
Spread over croutons.
Sprinkle cheese next.
Mix together milk, soup, eggs and mustard.
Pour over sausage and croutons.
Saute mushrooms, arranging on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and nuts.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Stir often so that mixture makes its own juice. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to apple mixture and add oil, vanilla and eggs. Stir by hand (not mixer).
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes; loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Peel and dice when they are cool.
Dice cheese, pimento, green pepper, onion and oleo.
Break up bread.
Mix all ingredients except milk.
Put into buttered casserole.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together, place in a serving bowl, and chill. Serve cold.

title: tasty birds nests
directions: Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; shape into bird's nests. Add candy for eggs.
Eat and enjoy!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add thawed shrimp, garlic powder and lemon juice.
Beat together until smooth.
Add a small can of shrimp.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: old-fashioned lemon cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour the bottoms of two 9-inch cake pans.
Beat the egg whites until stiff but not dry. In large bowl, combine shortening, sugar and vanilla. Beat until well mixed. In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir to mix.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the ice water.

Fold in the beaten egg whites. Spoon into prepared pans. Bake about 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of each layer. Remove from pans and cool completely on a rack.
Spread with Lemon Cheese Icing.

title: deer sausage
directions: Mix and form in rolls; wrap in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Add 2 cups hot water to baking dish.
Bake 1
1/2 hours.
Drain rolls and re-wrap for freezer.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, yolks and sugar at high speed for 2 minutes.
Add cornmeal, flour, lemon juice and rind. Mix well.
Pour into pie crust and bake 30 minutes.
Allow to cool to room temperature.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Note:
If using self-rising flour omit baking powder and salt.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and mix in vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop from a spoon onto waxed paper or a
buttered cookie sheet.
Let stand for 1 hour until cooled.

title: white chocolate brownie drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat first four ingredients until smooth. Add melted chocolate; mix well.
Stir in combined dry ingredients and white chocolate.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are almost set. (Centers should still be moist, do not overbake.)
Cool 2 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift and stir flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with moist fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Put a thin confectioners sugar icing on when cool.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook beef and chicken until well done, grind all ingredients. Put into large pot, bring to a slow boil. Add 3 sticks margarine. Salt and pepper to taste. Keeps well in freezer.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spread out on buttered cookie sheet.
Let harden.

title: no-fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and water in saucepan; stir until it thickens and is clear.
Let stand until completely cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, vanilla, salt and cooled cornstarch mixture.
Beat until stiff.
Spread over cooled pie. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Tops one 9-inch pie pan.

title: hearty oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.

title: mother's sweetheart cookies
directions: Beat together butter and cream cheese until creamy.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat again.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamy mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts; mix well. Chill several hours.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Cook beef until crumbly and drain.
Add corn, onion, bell pepper and taco seasoning mix to meat.
Stir in water and simmer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Add taco mix.
Add tomatoes and corn.
Bring to soft boil.
Pour into dish.
Carefully top with corn bread batter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Mix together beef and pork.
Soak bread in milk; add egg to bread mix.
Add spices and onion; work together well.
Roll into balls size of walnut.
Brown in pan in olive oil.
Move into casserole.
Cover with water and soy sauce.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Thicken gravy with flour; stir in water.
Simmer a few minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine spinach, zucchini, cottage cheese, mushrooms, carrots, onions, eggs and Parmesan cheese. Mix well. Alternate layers of sauce, noodles, Mozzarella cheese and mixture in a 13 x 9 nonstick baking pan. Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is melted. Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Will make a stiff dough.
Bake in mini muffin tins sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 48 to 50 muffins.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk and bring to a scald.
Stir into the egg mixture fast.
Toast 6 slices of bread if thin slices (use 4 if thick slices).
Butter and cut into squares; press into the milk.
This will fit into a 2-quart casserole, greased.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then lower oven to 350° for 30 minutes.
Shake cinnamon on top.

title: barbecue bean salad
directions: Open, drain and rinse beans.
Drain well in colander.
Place in 2-inch deep container that can be covered in refrigerator.
Add pepper, parsley, onion, sliced thin and separated into rings.

title: crock pot chicken and dressing
directions: May need to add 1/2 to 3/4 c. more broth as needed.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add chicken, soup, tomatoes, salt and garlic powder.
Add cooked spaghetti and mix well.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake in 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pat's baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add sour cream or yogurt and mix like pie crust.
Then add milk and knead 14 times; pat and cut.
Makes 5 to 6 large biscuits.
Bake 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: icebox cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into long rolls.
Wrap tightly in waxed paper and place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Skin and wash chicken; salt.
Dip chicken in melted margarine or oil.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Put in baking pan.
Bake in covered pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together the first 9 ingredients; form into walnut-size balls.
Roll in flour.
Heat very small amount of oil in large skillet.
Brown balls over low heat and cook through.
Transfer to casserole.
Add sour cream and milk to pan drippings and stir; spoon over cooked meat balls.
Serve 4 to 6 for dinner, more as appetizers.

title: lasagna 2
directions: Brown sausage and beef, then drain.
Add all ingredients, except noodles; simmer 30 minutes to an hour.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, zucchini, oil and vinegar together.
Mix dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in two greased and floured bread pans.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Cover bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan with blueberries and sprinkle with sugar.
Mix together rest of ingredients and pour over berries.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: gak
directions: Mix glue and 3/4 cup water together in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, add Borax to 1/3 cup water, little at a time.
Add Borax mixture to glue mixture, little at a time.
Great for kids to play with.
Won't stick to carpet and furniture.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soda and popcorn in a glass bowl and bring to a boil; continue to microwave on Full power for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda.
Put popped corn in brown grocery bag.
Pour cooked mixture over corn, close bag and shake. Cook in bag on High in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes; shake and cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Check to see if coated well.
If not, shake another 1 to 2 minutes.

title: zippy onion dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add onion, salt and garlic powder. Use enough cold water to make the consistency you prefer. Cover tightly and keep in the refrigerator.

title: jalapeno jellygroves, texas
directions: Seed peppers and grind or chop.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonful into hot oil in large frying pan. Flatten out patties. Cook until golden brown.
Turn over and brown on other side.

title: dill dip 1
directions: Mix.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: crab or shrimp cheese block
directions: Put the block of cream cheese on serving plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over cheese until well covered.
Put drained meat on top so that it looks neat.
Serve with any variety of crackers.

title: bye-bye blues soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add the carrots and leek; add meat stock.
Place all in a large pan with other vegetables.
Simmer over slow fire for 1 to 2 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: brown sugar shortbread cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Gradually stir in the flour.
Knead in bowl for 3 minutes.
Roll into small balls; place 1-inch apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Do not dip fork in water or flour.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or just until bottom of cookies begin to brown.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese rings
directions: Work together all ingredients. Form into small balls.
Press flat on cookie sheet with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: filling for nasturtiums
directions: Soften cream or cottage cheese. Add other ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Pick, wash, dry blooms.
Stuff.
Fold ends together and eat-eat-eat.
If you want to use fresh blooms another day, put in bowl of water in refrigerator.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Combine in souffle dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Serve with onion rounds and enjoy!

title: pineapple banana supreme
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and melted butter. Pat into 8 x 12-inch dish to form crust.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and 7-Up, then pineapple and mashed bananas.
Let set until partly jelled.
Pour over graham cracker crust.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 15 minutes.
Stir gently.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup crushed tortilla chips and 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Garnish with shredded lettuce and ripe olive slices.

title: casserole
directions: Put in a Pyrex dish a layer of Tater Tots, layer of hamburger and a layer of green beans.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Repeat ingredients again.
You may add onions or whatever to season. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except the nuts) and form a ball. Roll in the nuts until evenly coated. Chill until serving time.

title: "you can't get enough cake"
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Remove from oven and punch holes in cake while still hot (using a wooden spoon handle).
Pour 1 can sweetened condensed milk over cake.
Pour caramel topping over cake while still hot.
Add 1/2 Heath bar pieces.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip to top of cooled cake.
Sprinkle remaining Heath bar pieces to top of Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix together and
pour
into
pie crust.
First 10 minutes, bake at 400°, then reduce to 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix together the sugar, Crisco and salt.
Add boiling water and eggs.
Let cool.
In a measuring cup, measure warm water and yeast. Add to the mixture.
Add flour.
Mix and set in the refrigerator at least 4 hours.
Roll rolls and cut them as you want them.
Let rise at least 3 hours.
Bake at 400° to 450°.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer slowly at least 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Stir and cook until slightly thickened.
Add:

title: green beans and artichokes
directions: Combine green beans and artichokes.
Blend other ingredients. Pour over bean mixture.
Marinate 24 hours.
Heat in marinade and serve.

title: chicken paprika
directions: In baking dish place chicken.
Sprinkle paprika over.
Mix together soup, sour cream, mushrooms, wine and water chestnuts. Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: crusty fried oysters
directions: Combine egg and water.
Dip oysters in egg mixture and roll each in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot oil (375°) for about 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning to brown both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield:
3 servings.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients just before baking.
Top with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils; drain and place in soup kettle.
Add 8 cups water and remaining ingredients, except tomatoes and vinegar. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes (break up any large pieces) and vinegar.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes longer. Season to taste.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Remove fat and bone from meat and cut in strips, 1/4 inch wide and 1 1/2 inches long.
Brown meat in shortening in heavy skillet. Transfer meat to a 2-quart casserole and add raw onion, salt, pepper and bouillon.
Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally if meat on top becomes dry.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Cream in bananas.
Add eggs, vanilla and soda; stir well.
Stir flour into mixture.
Add nuts. Pour mixture into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine chicken broth, onion and asparagus. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until asparagus is tender.
Place mixture in blender.
Cover and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in vegetable puree.
Cook until heated through.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook until thickened, except the beets.
When thickened, pour over diced beets and stir together.

title: old country supper
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove.
Slice potatoes and fry in bacon drippings until golden brown.
Resist the temptation to stir too often.
Let them brown before turning.

title: coffee punch
directions: In the morning, mix coffee and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Add milk and vanilla.
Chill several hours.
When ready to serve, in large punch bowl, put in ice cream, pour coffee mixture over it.
Top with dabs of whipped cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Use jelly roll pan.

title: ham and asparagus bows
directions: Cook the pasta in boiling water in large Dutch oven according to the package directions, except add the frozen asparagus or broccoli the last 5 minutes and the ham the last minute of the cooking time.
Drain and return to the pan.

title: omelet(for 6 to 8 people)
directions: Brown hash brown potatoes on both sides.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Beat eggs; pour over hash browns, then layer green peppers over the eggs, then also onions and mushrooms.
Fry a few strips of bacon or cut ham and layer over that and add shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and browns and eggs are cooked.

title: tallerene
directions: Cook noodles.
Sear meat and chopped onion until grainy. Drain grease.
Add half the catsup, half the cheese, and all the other ingredients.
Put in 3 or 3 1/2 quart casserole dish and top with remaining catsup and cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375° or 400° until bubbly.
Can be frozen as is.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas into crust and spread softened ice cream on top. Freeze for 2 hours.
Spread preserves on top of the ice cream. Then spread chocolate sauce, then Cool Whip, cherries, then nuts. Keep refrigerated.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain; add package of chili mix and stir well. Add tomato sauce and water. Cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Stirring occasionally. Pour corn chips into a 9x9x2 inch baking dish. Cover corn chips with meat mixture and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheeses melts.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt.
Beat egg; add water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture.
(You may have to add a little more water.)
Divide dough.
Roll on floured cloth or board.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage in loose pieces.
Add chopped onion and pepper. Saute over low heat until tender.
Drain grease; set aside.
Roll out dough.
Place sausage and vegetables on top of the dough.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle on onion and/or garlic salt to taste.
Roll up dough.
Brush top with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Butter bread, cut off crust, place upside down in 13 x 9 pan sprayed with Pam. Mix milk with soup. Pour ingredients in casserole and top with cheese. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Combine butter and shortening in a large bowl; beat well with electric mixer.
Add flavorings and salt.
Gradually add sugar, 1 cup at a time.
Add whipping cream to creamed mixture, beating until smooth enough to spread.

title: indian fried eggplant
directions: In a baking dish, place a layer of sliced raw potatoes, then some chopped onion. Repeat layers. Mix a can of Cheddar cheese soup with a little water and pour over potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Pour all ingredients (after mixing) into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Warm in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients and drain, then put in casserole and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: a very good church
directions: Use a batter of Honesty.
Add an overflowing cup of concern for all people.
Sprinkle on thoroughly the religious morality. Mix in hard work and dedication.
Bake in an oven of compassion and happiness.
Top with principles of the Golden Rule.
Serve with equal portions of love for all.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: You will need a cooking bag also.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Heat oil in cast-iron pot; add flour and stir constantly until dark roux is obtained.
Add both cans of soup, tomato sauce and herbs; simmer and cook on low heat for about 30 minutes, adding small amounts of water as needed.
(Caution:
you want this gravy pretty thick.)
Add seasoning spices and shrimp; allow to cook for 30 minutes longer.
Makes 8 hearty servings.

title: cowboy eggs
directions: Cook bacon. Add potatoes and sausage.
Fry until nearly done and add bell pepper and onion.
Cook until soft. Pour in eggs. When eggs are scrambled, turn off and add cheese. Let melt. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: golden hamburger
directions: Put in baking dish as listed.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: triple citrus chiffon cake with lemon custard
directions: Prepare Lemon Custard and cool.
Grease and line three 9-inch cake pans.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and egg yolks, then mix in lemon juice. Pour into pie crust and let set for 15 minutes.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix blueberries
and
cup
sugar and let stand overnight. Sift
flour,
baking powder, salt and 1 1/2 cups sugar into bowl and
make a well.
Add buttermilk and eggs to flour mixture.
Add to
batter browned butter and shortening.
Fold in
blueberries. Use
greased
muffin
tins for best results, although paper liners can be used.
Bake at 400° approximately 25 minutes, until brown. (I don't know how many it makes, but plenty.)

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing and cheese.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill before eating.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate for 1 hour, allowing flavors to blend. Serve with baked, broiled or fried fish and seafood or salmon or tuna croquettes.

title: williams prize winning meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 10 x 6-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 1 hour. Drain and let stand 5 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, press raw hamburger flat.
Spread soup on top.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
We sometimes add a layer of canned or frozen peas before the Tater Tots.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.	Yield:	12 to 16 servings.

title: green peas and onions
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over a low fire for 10 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: italian tomato soup
directions: Combine soup, milk, butter and sugar in a heavy saucepan. Heat.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick the reserved pineapple juice, egg, sugar, vinegar and flour.
Refrigerate to cool.
When this mixture is cool, combine with all other ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Wash leg of lamb and pat dry.
Use sharp knife to make small holes in lamb.
Cut garlic in slices and place a slice in each hole.
Put small sprigs of rosemary in hole with garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Roast in a covered roaster at 325° for about 2 hours or until done to your liking.

title: italian beef stew
directions: Place beef in a skillet with the onion and brown about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, sauce, water, carrots and celery and cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Put the diced potatoes in the last 30 minutes. Serves about 12.

title: apple skillet pie(first place winner)
directions: Peel, core and halve the apples.
Place apples in a bowl and toss with lemon juice.
Pour sugar into heavy large cast iron skillet.
Add water to cover.
Cook sugar and water until it turns blonde in color.
Add oleo.
Sugar will crystallize.
Remove from heat; add apples, standing on end around skillet.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Remove from heat; place sheet of puff pastry over top. Trim.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Remove and cool 15 minutes.
Place plate over pie and invert onto plate.
Glaze with flavor of choice.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put dill in bottom, then spears.
Make brine of vinegar, water and salt.
Boil with dill.
Top with lid; pack.
Let stand for 6 weeks.
Shake every little while.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition. In a bowl, sift together flour, baking power and salt.
Add with milk to the sugar and butter mixture.
Stir by hand to moisten all ingredients completely.
Stir in chopped cranberries.
Spoon into 18 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: garden fresh salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cook the rotini and rinse with cool water to chill.
Add to vegetables. In a small mixing bowl, combine the last 5 ingredients.
Pour over rotini vegetable mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings or 2 quarts.

title: russian borache(beet soup)
directions: Shred all vegetables.
Add pork, salt, pepper and vinegar; cover with water.
Cook 3 hours.
Remove pork; cut into small pieces.
Return to soup after it stops boiling.
Add 2 pints sour cream.

title: leftover turkey chowder
directions: Heat all ingredients except scallions in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Do not boil.
When hot, add scallions and serve.

title: lemon of a dream dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and almonds (optional).
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool

title: date torte
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder into first mixture.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
I usually double this recipe and use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: schrafft's chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter; add flour and paprika.
Blend.
Slowly add chicken stock, cream and milk, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat.
Remove from stove and add egg yolks, chicken, mushrooms, salt and pimento strips.
Can be served over toast or patty shells.

title: canadian spread for snacks(corton)
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot; add water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat to medium; stir occasionally and cook until meat starts to stick to bottom of pan.
After all water has evaporated, the liquid left is fat and your corton is done.
Pour mixture in jars or pan and refrigerate until cold.
Some remove most fat that settles on top when corton is chilled, other leave it on.
Spread on crackers to serve or French Tourtiers (pork pies) with corton.
Put some of the filling between two pie crusts and bake at 450° until done (about 20 minutes).
Tourtiers may be frozen and reheated at 350°.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Slowly melt the butter and chocolate chips.
Remove from heat. Stir in eggs and nuts.
Cool.
Gradually add marshmallows, mixing well after
each addition.
Divide mixture into 3 rolls.
Roll each in confectioners sugar.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate. Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugars and butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chili pork
directions: Sprinkle chili powder, instant coffee, salt and pepper evenly on sliced pork tenderloin.
Place in a plastic bag or in a bowl and marinate at least one hour or up to overnight.
To prepare, melt one tablespoon of butter in nonstick skillet.
Saute marinated tenderloin over a high flame until the meat is grey all the way through (if the spice and coffee start to burn, a small amount of liquid, either water or broth, may be added).
Remove meat from skillet.
If more than one batch is needed, continue until all meat is done.
Store the done meat in a warm oven until the sauce is completed.
To the drippings in the pan, add the last tablespoon of butter.
After the butter has melted, add the cup of vermouth and continue to heat until the liquid is reduced by half.
This goes great with Jalapeno Cheese Grits.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Lay the chicken breasts in a casserole dish.
Mix the apricot preserves, barbecue sauce and soup mix.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chewy chocolate cookie
directions: In a large bowl, blend sugar, margarine and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Mix in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to chocolate mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Cover and chill for 2 hours. Drop by teaspoonful into confectioners sugar, coating lightly. Then shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mom's cucumber tsukemono
directions: Boil 1 1/2 cups water and 1/4 cup Hawaiian salt until salt is completely dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain and pack loosely in jars.
Mix sugar, vinegar, 1 1/2 cups water, garlic and chili pepper.
Pour over cucumbers and refrigerate.

title: dairy queen ice cream
directions: Soak gelatin in the cold water.
Heat milk until hot, but not boiling; remove from heat.
Add gelatin, sugar, vanilla and salt. Cool.
Add cream.
Put in icebox to chill 5 to 6 hours before freezing.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: bing bars
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and stir until full boil (scorches easily).
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from fire and add cherry chips.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
Add topping.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples and fill with butter, cinnamon and marshmallows. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken olive-ia
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole.
Combine sour cream, olives, onions, chilies and soup; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or microwave on Medium for 20 minutes, covered.
May be served over rice.

title: chicken pie
directions: Add vegetables to water; simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1/2 pound cheese, cubed.
Stir until melted.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Spoon mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Prepare pie crust as directed on package.
Roll dough into 7-inch circle.
Divide into sixths. Place over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese, sliced.
Continue baking until melted.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Tear angel food cake into small pieces.
Make a layer of angel food cake in the bottom of the cake pan (use about half of cake).
Next, pour half the batter mixture over angel food crumbs.
Sprinkle on a layer of crushed Butterfingers. Repeat layers until all of mixture is used.
Sprinkle with remainder of the crushed Butterfingers on top.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Place potatoes, sausage, peppers and onions over meat.
Pour lemon juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger stuffed bread
directions: Cut top of bread lengthwise.
Gently hollow out inside forming a 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick crust shell.
Reserve hollowed out bread. Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.

Add all remaining ingredients except cheese slices. Simmer for about 5 minutes. Tear hollowed out bread into small pieces, making 2 cups. Add to meat mixture. Fill bread crust shell with meat and bread mixture. Cut cheese slices in half diagonally.
Place over top of mixture. Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts. Replace top of bread and serve.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Beat, then pour into a pie plate and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn down to 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: rye bread toasties
directions: Brown meats and drain. Cube cheese and add to meats. Stir until cheese melts. Spread on bread slices.
Freeze on cookie sheets and then place in bags.
Cook while frozen.
Broil until bubbly.

title: veggies
directions: Saute vegetables, any amount you want, in chicken broth until crisp-tender (except tomatoes).
Add tomatoes, salt and sugar. Cook on low heat until it looks like soup.
Serve with cornbread.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix and spread on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan (spray pan with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: heavenly strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; stir into strawberry juice.
Add lemon juice and cook until thickened.
Set aside to cool.

title: party mashed potatoes
directions: Bring milk, water and oleo to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add potatoes to liquid mixture, stir and let set.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add potatoes to cream mixture and beat until fluffy.
Add salt and garlic.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut a few pats of butter on top and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add juice from fruit. Cool in refrigerator.
Add fruit and let jell.
Place marshmallows completely over top.
Mix Cool Whip and mayonnaise; spread over top of marshmallows.
Let set (overnight is best) before serving.

title: easy homemade rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over oleo, sugar and salt.
Let set until oleo is completely melted.
Add beaten egg to mixture.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to other ingredients.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours; dough may be kept in refrigerator until needed, up to 10 days.
Keep well covered.
Put in greased pan, shaped as desired.
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours in warm place.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: In a large boiler, brown chuck and round.
Add large onion. Add garlic powder, garlic salt and celery.	Add bean sprouts. Next add water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.
Add soy sauce.
Pour into large baking pan.
Sprinkle noodles on top.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: salt pork beans and hominy
directions: Wash the beans, cover with water and let soak overnight. Cover hominy with water; also, let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain off water from both.
Combine beans and hominy and cover with fresh cold water.
Wash the salt pork and lay in strips on the top.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and add a pinch of sweet marjoram.
Let mixture cook slowly for about 5 hours, adding more water as necessary.

title: fourth of july cake
directions: One hour ahead:
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pans; line with wax paper, grease paper. Prepare cake batter according to package directions, working with one package at a time.
Spread batter in prepared pans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Invert cake layers onto wire racks.
Peel off paper; cool.

title: easy mexican dish
directions: Line dish with chips.
Brown meat and drain grease.
Add all other ingredients to meat and mix together.
Pour mixture over chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bobby's hot fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over very low heat.
Stir in sugar and pudding mix about 1 cup at a time, being sure it is blended before adding more.
Mixture will become very thick and dry.
Add salt and stir in milk gradually.
Continue to cook 7 or 8 minutes to blend and dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Serve hot or cold over ice cream or cake.

title: little pizzas
directions: Cook sausage until pink is gone.
Cut up cheese and add, stirring, until cheese is melted.
Stir in onion and seasoning mix. Mix well.
Spread on rye bread and bake at 400° for 6 minutes. If you want to freeze, after spreading, set in freezer until hard, then pack in bags.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Simmer onion and butter.
Add flour, milk and Cheez Whiz to onion; cook until thick.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Cook broccoli for a few minutes; drain and add to first mixture.
Pour into greased pan; cover with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add pecans last.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set in center.

title: sandies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and flour.
Add pecans and mix well.
Form small rolls 1 1/2-inches long.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and water with rest of ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese; add chopped onions, chillies and corn.
Put in 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 25 minutes.
This can be topped with seasoned bread crumbs before baking.

title: crabmeat horseradish spread
directions: Mix well.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: gram farleigh's baked beans
directions: Cook beans until practically done, then add baking soda to make cook faster.
Drain beans.
Add brown sugar and ketchup until dark.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 400° until tastes done.

title: favorite broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion, tomato and eggs.
Set aside.
In another bowl combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix until smooth.
Just before serving pour dressing over salad and toss well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate caramel sundaes
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir milk duds and milk until smooth.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on cake mix.
Cool cake 20 minutes.
Whip cream cheese, milk and vanilla pudding and put on cake.
Mix crushed pineapple with Cool Whip and spread over top of cake.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Use a 15 x 10-inch baking pan.

title: easy chocolate peppermint pie
directions: Place patties and milk in bowl.; Microwave 1 minute on High. Stir and cool slightly. Fold into Cool Whip, then into crust. Cover and freeze several hours.

title: midwest morning caramel ring
directions: Add sugar, corn syrup and nuts to melted butter.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat immediately.
Spray Bundt pan with nonstick coating or coat with 3 tablespoons margarine.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown all the meat.
Melt cheese. Mix all together.
Spread on small rye slices or English muffins. Cook in a 400° oven until bubbly and brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and undissolved active dry yeast.
Combine buttermilk, water and shortening in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Shortening does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally,
or with rotary beater.
Add 3/4 cup flour or enough flour to make a thick batter.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.

title: christmas tea cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt, then chopped walnuts.
Chill dough 1 hour. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool and roll again in confectioners sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple rolls(so very good)
directions: Cook sugar, water, cinnamon, butter and nutmeg in pan.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and shortening.
Cut in milk.
Knead 5 times.
Roll into rectangle.
Spread shredded apples over dough.
Roll beginning at long side.
Cut into 12 slices. Place in greased 13 x 9 pan.
Pour syrup over slices.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: basic wild game pot roast
directions: Pour cooking oil into bottom of large Dutch oven to cover bottom.
Rinse meat well and coat liberally with seasoning.
Heat oil over medium heat and place pieces of meat in oil to brown. Important:
The browning of the meat will seal in flavor and help make the gravy.
Do not allow to become too hot or the bottom of your pan will burn.
After all pieces are well browned, return to pot.
Press out garlic and add chopped onion.
Pour in water until just below the level of meat.
Cook over medium-high heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until tender.
Serve with large pot of rice. Better the 2nd day!

title: buffalo wings
directions: Wash chicken wings; add seasoning (seasoned salt, garlic and pepper).
Fry in skillet without flour.
Let brown on both sides. Take out.
In small pot, add butter/margarine and Tabasco sauce together.
Heat until butter is melted, then place chicken wings in a pan and pour sauce over drummettes.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Put in casserole dish with cubed cheese and all but approximately 1 cup crushed crackers.
Pour milk over all so ingredients are approximately 3/4 covered.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and top with remaining crackers mixed with melted butter.
Cover casserole and bake at 375° for 1 hour and uncovered approximately 1 hour.

title: stuffed hasu
directions: Spread	approximately 1 tablespoon of mix on each slice of Hasu
and
flatten.
Dip in flour, then egg and fry in oil until brown.

title: orange juice pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend for 15 seconds.
For medium-large pancakes, use 1/4 cup batter for each pancake and bake on lightly oiled griddle or skillet, turning once, until golden brown.

title: shrimp, herbs and pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain, set aside and keep
warm.
In
a
large
cast-iron
skillet,
melt butter over medium-high heat and add shrimp, garlic and onion. Cook, stirring constantly, about 4 minutes.
Remove shrimp and set aside, then add the half and half to the garlic and onions in skillet; bring to a
boil, reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes, continuing to
stir.
Return
shrimp
and add parsley and seasonings; stir
until
blended.
Serve
over
the cooked pasta. Yield: 2 servings.

title: doughnuts(cake type)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and milk.
Sift flour; add baking powder, salt, soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Sift twice more.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture gradually and beat well.
Chill. Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and fry.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll in sugar.
Makes about 40 doughnuts.

title: coffee time doughnuts
directions: Combine 1/4 cup warm water and package of dry yeast.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir to blend.
Combine the boiling water, scalded milk, shortening and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg, nutmeg and dissolved yeast.
Mix well.
Stir in sifted flour.
Mix to soft dough.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Roll and cut.
Let rise about 40 minutes.
Fry and glaze.

title: million dollar fudge(easy!)
directions: After the chocolate melts and all the ingredients are combined, you may want to add one or more of the following:
2 cups nutmeats, raisins, coconut or other goodies.

title: french carrot soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan and saute the onion.
Add potatoes and carrots and stir-fry for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add broth, cover the pan and simmer for 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: stir-fried rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Add eggs and cook without stirring until set. Turn eggs out onto a baking sheet and slice into strips.

title: swiss beans
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour and stir.
Add sour cream and chopped onion.
Heat to thicken.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; set aside.
Mix drained green beans and grated Swiss cheese in casserole dish.
Add sour cream sauce and stir to blend ingredients.
Bake in 375° oven until bubbling, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: extra good macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Fold in macaroni and spoon into greased casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, covered, and an additional 15 minutes, covered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: big pancake
directions: Melt butter in glass pie plate.
Combine egg, flour and milk in blender or shaker.
Pour mixture into center of melted butter. Bake for approximately 20 minutes in preheated oven at 375°.

title: holiday olive spread
directions: Add nuts to processing bowl and pulse until finely chopped. Add olives and finely chop.
Add cheese, 2 ounces at a time and process until mixed.
Remove and garnish with olives.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: weird salad
directions: Toss first 8 ingredients together.
Mix sugar and vinegar; pour over salad and toss.

title: mom's chocolate chip chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Make a well; add oil, egg yolks, water, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat until smooth.
In large bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff.
Pour egg mixture gradually over whites.
Blend in one square of finely grated unsweetened chocolate.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Invert and hang until cool.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix coconut with sugar and 2/3 cup butter.
Make about 60 (1-inch) balls.
Refrigerate until firm.
Dip in semi-sweet chocolate which has been melted along with 1/4 cup butter.
Place on wax paper on cookie sheet in refrigerator until served.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, fill about half full of water.
Add ground beef; let cook, then add potatoes, mixed vegetables, tomatoes and onion.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Cool and serve.

title: sugar-free chocolate fudge
directions: Melt the chocolate and cool.
Beat the cream cheese, sweetener and vanilla until smooth.
Add chocolate and beat.
Add pecans. Pour into an 8-inch square pan lined with foil.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 16 squares.
Served chilled.

title: orange-cream cheese cups
directions: Drain pineapple.
Keep syrup.
Add hot water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.

title: candied grapefruit peel
directions: Cut grapefruit peel into desired shapes and sizes of triangles. Place in large cooking pot and cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 20 minutes; drain.
Return the grapefruit to pot and cover with hot water.
Bring to boil and boil 20 minutes. Drain and return to pot.
Cover with hot water; bring to a boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Weigh the hot grapefruit and add an equal weight of sugar.
If using color, add now.
Stir well and cook over medium heat to medium-high until liquid is absorbed.
Be careful near end.
Roll in sugar and put on rack to cool and dry. Store with wax paper between layers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of pie filling after sprinkling cinnamon over filling.
Sprinkle cinnamon over cake mix.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: baked fish
directions: Place sliced potatoes and onions in a baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together tomato juice, pepper, flour and water and pour over potatoes and onions.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° until potatoes are almost done.
Place fish on top of potatoes and cook 15 minutes longer or until done.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in 3 cups flour and lemon extract. Mix fruit, nuts and rest of flour in separate bowl.
Add to batter.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground meat in skillet.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Stir until hot.
Pour in oblong pan and top with grated cheese.
Put in a 350° oven until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: ice cream mix
directions: Beat eggs really good; add sugar and beat some more.
Add Eagle Brand milk; beat.
Add Pet milk and beat.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Add homogenized milk to fill line. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: mexican praline candy
directions: Cook brown sugar, milk, syrup and pecans together to hard ball stage.
Cook over meduim heat in heavy pan; stir and watch closely.
Remove from heat; add oleo and cream of tartar.
Allow to cool.
Place waxed paper over cloth.
Beat candy and pour by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Wrap individually in waxed paper. Yield:
20 pieces.

title: caramel popcorn(baked)
directions: Spread popcorn in a large, shallow pan.
In a heavy 1 1/2-quart pan, stir together the margarine, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Continue cooking, without stirring, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn.
Stir to coat well.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cool and break apart.
Makes 1 pound.

title: chocolate topped rice krispie treats
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup in large saucepan on medium heat on stove.
Bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter, remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies.
Put into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together and pour over Rice Krispies. Best if refrigerated 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Boil chicken until tender and easily removed from the bones. Pour off stock and set aside. Saute in about 2 tablespoons of oil until all ropiness is gone (approximately 1/2 hour).

title: apple bread
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add apples.
Fold in cream mixture. Cook raisins in a little water for 5 minutes.
Add raisins to mixture.
Bake in three loaf pans (4 x 7 1/2-inch) greased and floured for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fresh cranberry sauce with oranges
directions: Wash berries.
Put sugar and water into a saucepan and stir until combined.
Bring to a boil.
Add cranberries, orange juice and orange.
Simmer until the berries become soft.
Cool.
Pour into a bowl and refrigerate several hours.

title: deluxe banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Blend sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs and bananas.
Gradually add dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon juice and beat 2 minutes longer.
Fold in nuts, 3/4 by hand.
Pour batter in a greased pan.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top of loaf and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix relish and mayonnaise.
Mix with all ingredients.

title: pumpkin chiffon
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: thanksgiving mountain grouse
directions: Defrost breasts overnight in large roasting pan with cold water and Tender Quick.
Rinse birds off and pan out thoroughly in morning.
Combine soy sauce and Five Spice into bowl until a granulated consistency occurs.
Rub mixture deeply into breasts. Strip bacon to cover bottom of roasting pans and add breasts. Cover and refrigerate until ready to cook.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: Remove meat to warm plate.
Pan-fry mushrooms in the drippings. Add flour to drippings in pan; stir.
Add water and bouillon cube. Cook until mixture boils, cube is dissolved and sauce is thick.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, sugar and salt mixture.
Beat egg in measuring cup and add enough milk to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Add with vinegar to shortening mixture.
This makes about 3 pie crusts.
The vinegar in the crust gives it a nice bronze color when cooked.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together. Cut out center of round loaf of unseeded bread (rye, pumpernickel, etc.). Hollow out bread. Fill with dip and place pieces of bread around it for dipping.

title: herbed beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, sugar, cheese and herbs. Mix well.
Stir in beer to make stiff batter.
Grease loaf pan with shortening.
Sprinkle bottom and sides with cornmeal.
Turn batter into pan and bake at 325° for 65 minutes.
Brush baked loaf with butter.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: split pea soup
directions: Put peas, water and salt in large kettle. Bring to a strong boil, then turn heat down. Simmer for 1/2 hour before adding other ingredients. That way you can skim the froth off (to reduce gas bubbles in the finished product). After skimming away froth, add onions, celery and butter and continue simmering at least 1 hour more.
Freezes well.

title: apricot nut cups
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter or margarine into flour with a pastry blender.
For easier handling, chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Form into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Line miniature muffin pans with balls of dough and shape into crusts.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in the jacket in salted water until tender, but not falling apart.
When cool enough to handle, peel, slice and layer in a buttered casserole with bell pepper, pimentos, and lemon pepper in each layer.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Melt cheese which has been cubed.
Cook until melted. Pour over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 450 degrees until golden brown.

title: pineapple angel pie
directions: Combine pineapple (fruit and juice), sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixed with water and cook until very thick, stirring all the while.
Cool.
Beat egg whites and fold in sugar. Fold into pineapple and turn into a baked pie shell.
Cover with the whipped cream.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and cherries.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in softened gelatin mixture until it is dissolved. Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in apples, nuts and celery.
Pour into 2-quart mold. Chill 12 hours or overnight.

title: beef roast
directions: Wrap loosely in heavy aluminum foil. Cook at 325° for 2 hours. Gravy will be made when roast is done.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain the spaghetti. While hot, stir in eggs, butter and Parmesan cheese. Shape into a buttered 10-inch pie plate. Top spaghetti with 15 ounces Prego spaghetti sauce. Spread pepperoni over pie. Sprinkle with 1 to 2 cups Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes and cut into wedges.

title: crab and noodle casserole
directions: Drain crab.
Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine with crab, drained noodles, sour cream, cottage cheese, grated cheese and seasonings.
Spoon into 6 individual buttered casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until piping hot.
Garnish with parsley.

title: potato griddle cakes
directions: Beat egg and a little milk, then add flour and remaining milk alternating while beating.
Allow to stand 2 hours.
Grate potatoes and add to batter.
Beat thoroughly and season.
Grease griddle or frypan and spread with thin layer of batter.
Brown both sides. Serve with fried salt side pork and/or lingonberries.

title: louisiana cream pralines
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add pecans and cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (234°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool 5 minutes.
Stir rapidly until mixture begins to thicken and coats pecans lightly. Drop rapidly from a teaspoon onto aluminum foil or lightly buttered baking sheet to form patties.
Let stand until cool and set.
Makes 44 small patties.
If candy becomes too stiff to handle easily stir in a few drops of hot water.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover beans with water; soak overnight.
Mix all ingredients. Bring to boil in pressure cooker for 40 minutes.
Bake in bean crock at 325° for 2 hours.

title: iron skillet corn bread
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Mix milk, beaten eggs and oil.
Add to dry mixture.
Mix thoroughly; beat several strokes.
Well oil an iron skillet; heat on medium heat and pour in batter.
Bake in preheated 435° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. This batter may also be cooked in well-oiled muffin pans.
Bake muffins 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook 1 cup

brown sugar, margarine and milk until bubbly. Blend in egg yolks, cornstarch and 1 1/2 cups milk. Cook until thickened. Pour into baked pie shell. Beat 2 eggs whites until stiff, beat in 2 Tbsp. brown sugar. Spread on pie, bake 325 degrees until browned.

title: crab cheese hors  d'oeuvres
directions: Mix softened cheese, butter and mayonnaise; add crab meat. Spread on muffins (split in halves), cut halves in fourths and freeze.
To serve, bake in 350° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Chop mushrooms, including stems; saute with onion in butter or margarine for 10 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Stirring constantly, add milk and chicken stock.
Cook until thick.
Add sherry just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread undrained
crushed
pineapple
into
13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Spread
cherry pie filling evenly over pineapple. Dump cake
mix
evenly
over pie filling.
Spread pecans over mixture.
Slice
butter
or margarine into pats and place on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add to sour cream.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: grandma's cinnamon rolls
directions: Cook sugar, flour and milk in heavy pan until 235° (soft ball).
Use a candy thermometer.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat; set pan in cold water.
Add vanilla and butter.
Let cool a little, then beat with a spoon until it looks like pie dough and can be kneaded.
(Length of time depends on weather.)
Place on plastic wrap; wrap it and knead until creamy.
Roll into 6-inch rolls and in cinnamon.
Store in airtight container lined with a paper towel.

title: chicken breasts with broccoli
directions: Cook chicken breasts for 20 minutes.
Remove bones.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions, but do not add salt.
Drain macaroni in colander; Rinse under cold water.

title: fullabull's cheese balls
directions: Mix sour cream and soup mix and add to softened cream cheese. Form into 2 balls and roll in nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: frozen cheese cake
directions: Cream salt, sugar and cream cheese together.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Pour into container lined with graham cracker crumbs. Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Freeze until firm.

title: deluxe cow patties
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium sauce pan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Add coconut and peanut butter. Drop on waxed paper with teaspoon.
Let cool. makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in heavy skillet.
Add onion, tomatoes, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and green pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Cook macaroni; drain and add to casserole.
Put all ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Fold in mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: kathy's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove the stems from the mushrooms, reserving the mushroom caps and chop the stems finely.
Saute stems with the garlic in 4 tablespoons of butter.
Add the bread crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Saute the mushroom caps briefly in 3 tablespoons of the remaining butter.
Fill the caps with the stuffing and place in a buttered shallow casserole. Melt the remaining butter and drizzle over the mushrooms.
Bake until very hot, about 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top and continue cooking for about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and preserved pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Let gel.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spinach salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, salt, Tabasco and vinegar.
Squeeze moisture from spinach.
Add spinach, eggs, celery, onion and cheese; mix well.
Store overnight in refrigerator so flavors will marry.
Makes eight 1/2-cup servings.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Slice potatoes and cook until done.
Preheat oven at 350°. Place ingredients into buttered baking dish as follows: potatoes, seasoning, onions, mayonnaise and cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday cheese logs
directions: Combine cheese and cream cheese, mixing until smooth.
Add pecans, olives and pimentos.
Chill.
Shape into 5 logs.
Roll in sesame seed, parsley or pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: beef and chicken teriyaki
directions: Cut beef and chicken in bite size pieces, saute in skillet until browned, then add garlic salt, 1/4 cup teriyaki sauce and 1/4 cup water and let simmer 15 minutes.
Then add vegetables and remaining sauce, let simmer 15 minutes longer.
Cook rice according to directions on box, serve mixture over rice.

title: chilled cherry cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle cracker crumbs on bottom of 8 inch square baking pan. Beat cheese, yogurt, sugar and vanilla in medium bowl with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Sprinkle gelatin into water in cup; let stand 2 minutes.
Microwave at High 40 seconds, stir and let stand 2 minutes or until gelatin is completely dissolved. Gradually beat gelatin mixture into cheese mixture with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan; refrigerate until firm.
Spoon cherry topping onto cheesecake.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: stromboli
directions: Sometimes we add mushrooms, onions and different cheeses inside roll too!

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Buds.
In large mixing bowl add vegetable oil, sugar and eggs; beat together until sugar is dissolved.
Add unprocessed bran, 2 cups flour, soaked Bran Buds, buttermilk, molasses, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Bake in muffin tins at 375° for 25 minutes.
Batter can be kept in covered container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: sausage-cheese bread
directions: Thaw dough and let rise.
Roll out flat.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Spread on dough; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and other cheese.
Roll up as a jelly roll and seal seam.
Place on a cookie sheet, and bake about 20 minutes after it rises the second time.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Save 1/2 to 1 cup.
Mix remaining cookies with melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Spread softened ice cream over crust.
Chill.
Then spread fudge topping over ice cream layer.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Freeze.

title: corn medley
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot; cook on low for about 2 hours.

title: jordan's peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt Butter in a pan on the stove.
Then add the Peanut Butter and stir until blended and melted with the butter.
Add Confectioners' Sugar and stir together until well blended and starts to take shape.
Put into a square pan.
Cool and cut.
I usually let cool overnight.
Then cut into pieces.

title: pineapple lime jello salad
directions: Add jello to 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 8 ice cubes; stir until melted.
Add drained pineapple.
Chill until firm.
In saucepan, add eggs, lemon juice and sugar.
Add pineapple juice and water to equal 1 cup.
Mix in cornstarch until thickened.
Let cool and spread on jello.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine, then mix all ingredients well and bake for about 35 minutes.
Add more broth if too dry.

title: beer battered fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a medium size bowl.
Beat in beer with a wire whisk until smooth.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Pour enough vegetable oil in a large skillet or a saucepan to make a depth of 1 inch.

Heat to 375° on a deep fat frying thermometer or until a cube of bread turns golden brown within about 60 seconds. Dip chicken pieces into beer batter, a few at a time, allowing excess to drain back into the bowl.
Fry chicken pieces, turning once, for 30 minutes or until chicken tests done.
Place on paper toweling to drain.
Keep warm in a very slow oven (250°) until all chicken is fried.
Garnish chicken with parsley and serve with onion rings.

title: czech dumplings
directions: Use a large mixing bowl.
Put flour in bowl.
Make a well in flour.
Put eggs, salt, baking powder and milk in well; mix.
Add bread cubes.
Mix well.
Let stand 1/2 hour.

title: scrambled pizza eggs
directions: Crumble sausage into a skillet.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook over medium heat until sausage is done.
Drain off drippings and discard.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, oregano and salt to skillet; simmer 10 minutes or until most of liquid evaporates, stirring often.
Add eggs and 1 3/4 cups cheese, stirring until eggs are set and cheese is melted, over medium heat.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese; serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in buttered dish.
Pour water over and sprinkle cinnamon and salt over apples.
Mix flour and sugar and cut in butter, blending until crumbly.
Spread over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about an hour.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in candies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: esther's peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together well.
Add peanut butter, blending until smooth.
Blend milk into the mixture, then whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Chill thoroughly.
Keep refrigerated.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add rice and toss until coated.
Add soups and seasoning.
Stir.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Stir once about 20 minutes before it's done. Serves 6 to 8.

title: finnan haddie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
For thin white sauce, melt butter in saucepan, add flour and stir to form paste.
Remove from heat and slowly add 1/2 the milk.
Return to
heat and stir until thickened; beat until smooth.
Gradually stir in remaining milk and heat to simmering.
Place fish in greased casserole dish and pour white sauce over it.
Cover and bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes, until fish flakes easily.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs which have been mixed with melted butter.
Return to oven and bake 5 to 10 minutes, until golden.
Sprinkle with parsley and garnish with lemon wedges.

title: cajun crabwich
directions: Mix crab, shrimp, mayonnaise, cream cheese and milk.
(Tuna salad consistency.)
Add spices.
Cut loaves down middle lengthwise; top with crab mix 1/2-inch thick.
Spread cheese and top with paprika.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.
Very Good.

title: broccoli-cauliflower toss
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces. Wash. Combine cauliflower, broccoli and onions. Toss gently. Combine remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour over vegetables. Toss gently. Cover and chill overnight.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Slowly add olive oil, stirring constantly, with a wire whisk until blended.
Serve over a green salad.
Yield: 2/3 cup.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in a bowl.
Stir in salt and oil.
Gradually stir in flour.
Smooth and knead until elastic.
Brush top with oil.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Roll out 2 pizzas.

title: wild rice and spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2-quart casserole.
Cook rice as directed, but use beef stock instead of water.
Thaw and warm spinach in microwave, then squeeze out water.
Mix with cream cheese until well mixed.
Saute mushrooms in butter and keep the juice.

title: dessert cups
directions: Mix together.
Put in cupcake papers in muffin tins and freeze.

title: sour cream donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then flour table and roll dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with donut cutter.
Fry in Crisco oil at 350° until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on brown paper bag until cool.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place cooked carrots in a casserole dish; pour mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit frosted pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Place dough slices, overlapping edges, on foil-lined 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake for 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Invert cooled crust onto serving plate and carefully remove foil.
Turn crust right side up.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Spread mixture over pizza crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.
Combine marmalade or preserves with water.
Spread over fruit topped pizza.
Chill well before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: shrimp mold appetizer spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Add gelatine to water, then put into hot undiluted soup.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the cream cheese mixture.
Put into oiled mold for at least 4 hours.
Best made the day ahead.

title: family favorite oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar and beat in eggs, flavoring and cream or milk.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together and mix with creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put into 2 casseroles (better if not too thick). Cover with topping of cornflakes and margarine. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Freezes well.

title: frogmore stuffed shrimp
directions: You will also need 40 rounded toothpicks and 1 flat grilling basket.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt over low heat 1 stick butter.
Add brown sugar.
Stir in eggs, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Use a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chest brownies
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients with a fork and press in an ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over first layer and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Watch crust last 5 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, spices and soda together and mix melted butter and applesauce together.
Add nuts and raisins.
Put in Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit and pudding compote
directions: Put milk and liqueur in bowl with pudding mix.
Beat on lowest speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip and beat 1 more minute.
Put most of fruit in serving bowl.
Top with pudding mixture.
Garnish with fruit and refrigerate.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, oil, eggs, zucchini, flour and vanilla in large bowl.
Add salt, baking powder, baking soda and oatmeal.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in nuts and spoon into greased 15 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 30 minutes. Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting, store bought or homemade.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Saute onions in butter (margarine).
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: water chestnut casserole
directions: Slice celery and place in baking dish.
Add soups and stir. Dice or slice water chestnuts.
Add to mixture.
Bake until boiling.
In a saucepan melt butter.
Crumble tube of crackers and place in pan with butter.
Place cracker mixture over celery mixture and bake on low heat for 5 minutes.
Top with sliced almonds, if desired.

title: danish able-kae
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch frypan.
Add crumbs and stir over medium heat until all crumbs are mixed well and browned lightly.
Mix sugar and cinnamon into crumbs.
Put 1/2 mixture into pan.
Cover well with applesauce (1/2 of the applesauce).
Then cover with the other half of crumbs, except save a few to sprinkle on top.
Then add rest of applesauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: mom's ugly brownies
directions: With an electric mixer, combine cake mix, margarine and two eggs.
Mixture will be thick.
Using your hands, place mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend together remaining eggs, sugar and creamed cheese with mixer.
Pour on top of brownies mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread entire package of cream cheese on bottom of 2-inch deep casserole dish.
Heat up chili and pour over cream cheese, covering it completely.
Put entire package of cheese on top of chili.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers, Doritos, etc.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together except green onion tops.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
After about 45 minutes cooking, stir and add seasoning, if needed.
When time is complete, remove from oven.
Add green onion tops and again check seasoning.

title: zeck's hebrew cake
directions: Pour into small bowl sour cream.
Sprinkle baking soda on top. Mix together cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Mix together flour and baking powder.
In large bowl, cream butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients except for cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Pour 1/2 batter.
Sprinkle with 1/3 bag of chocolate chips.
Sprinkle sugar mixture on top, pour rest of batter, 1/3 bag chocolate chips and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (deep pan).

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Let them cool, then cut into bite size pieces.
Put chicken in 2-quart baking dish.
Add soup, broth and Veg-All.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 30 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: cucumber-onion pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Cover with solution made from 1/2 cup salt and 2 quarts of water.
Weight down cucumbers and onions so all are covered completely.
Soak from 12 to 18 hours.
Drain off brine and discard.
Rinse cucumbers and onions with clear water.
Drain well.
Combine vinegar and new water, sugar and spices.
Bring to a rolling boil over high heat.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Simmer (but do not boil) until cucumbers and onions are heated through.
Cucumbers will lose bright green color. Pack loosely in jars and cover with solution they are cooked in. Seal and store.
Overcooking gives a soft pickle.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, celery seed and salt together; bring to a boil.
Pour over chopped cabbage and onion.
Mix well.

title: diabetic jelly
