directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan (except sweetener) ; bring to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add sweetener.
Pour in jar and store in refrigerator.
Yields 1 cup.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix pudding using 3 cups milk.
Chill until set.
Cream together cream cheese, oleo, sugar and Cool Whip.
Fold into pudding.
In a 2-quart flower pot, layer crushed Oreos and pudding, ending with a thick layer of Oreos (dirt).
Serve with hidden gummy worms.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook all together on low heat for 1 hour.
Serve on hamburg rolls.

title: louisiana pralines
directions: Place 2 cups sugar and milk in a large saucepan.
Cook slowly, stirring often.
At the same time, put other cup of sugar in another pan on low heat; stir until melted.
Pour slowly into the milk and sugar that should be ready to boil; stir while adding. Cook slowly until a firm ball forms in cold water (238°).
Set off heat.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Cook rice and mix
with remaining ingredients.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a well-greased casserole.

title: slow cooker oatmeal
directions: Grease slow cooker.
Combine all ingredients at bedtime.
Cook on low overnight for 8 to 10 hours.

title: ten minute lollipops
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add corn syrup and sugar. Cook to 275° or about 7 minutes. Make sure there are no lumps. Once cooked to 275° or 7 minutes, add gelatin. Stir until well blended. Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and place lollipop stick in center. Let cool completely and remove. Cover with plastic paper and tie ribbons around them. Very simple and fun.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Combine barbecue sauce, orange juice, brown sugar, oil, flour and salt; mix well.
Cook, stirring, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens slightly.
Add chicken, pineapple, water chestnuts and ginger; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix together Miracle Whip and sour cream or half and half.
Fold into macaroni mixture. Add salt and pepper to taste. Chill. Serve in lettuce cups.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix.
Store in covered container.
Use 1 heaping teaspoonfuls (or more if desired) to 1 cup hot water.

title: blitz torte
directions: Mix together all ingredients except egg whites and powdered sugar.
Beat powdered sugar into 2 tablespoons of stiff beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 2 greased layer cake pans.
Spread egg white mixture over batter.
Sprinkle tops with chopped walnuts. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until edges start to shrink.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven; brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Yield:
3 quarts.
This may be made in a crock-pot on low all day and enjoy for supper.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box (9 x 13 pan). Combine Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut. Punch fork holes in warm cake and pour liquid over cake. Let cake cool. Spread all of Cool Whip on cake and sprinkle with coconut. Store cake in refrigerator. Best if made the night before. Serves 12. Can do ahead.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Store in a jar and refrigerate.

title: grandma's pan cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and jam.
Beat thoroughly. Sift flour; measure and resift with soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes.
Ice with Caramel Frosting.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Blend egg, milk and oil.
Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt and add to liquid mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in blueberries (or other fruit).
Fill greased or lined muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Beat eggs in blender; add sugar. Margarine needs to be melted and cooled, then add.	Add flour, flavorings and salt.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Melt cranberry sauce in hot water.
Mix other ingredients and simmer until hot. You can refrigerate and serve as needed.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Bring to rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and skim top.
Add Certo and 8 to 10 drops food coloring.
Bring to hard boil for 1 minute.
Put jelly in jars and let seal.

title: hot bacon bites
directions: Crumble bacon; combine last 6 ingredients and spread mixture on rye bread.
Broil for 1 to 3 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash berries.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in 1 stick butter until crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
To remaining mix, add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine to the 1 cup of crumb mixture.
Sprinkle over muffins.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar free punch
directions: Mix Jell-O as instructed with boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and lemonade.
Freeze.
Thaw partially and add Sprite to make slushy.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well.
If too thin, add flour to thicken.
Pour into 2 pie shells, slightly browned, and bake 10 to 13 minutes at 325°.

title: savory chipped beef appetizer
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream together.
Stir in beef, onion and garlic powder.
Top with pecans and bake 20 minutes at 300°. Serve warm with rye bread rounds.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.

title: wild rice dressing
directions: Cook cornbread and set aside. Cook rice mix according to directions on package and set aside. Cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Mix together cornbread, cooked rice, dressing mix, cooked onions and celery. Season with poultry seasoning. Moisten with chicken broth. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: atrim banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding until thickened.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and topping.
Add lemon juice.
Layer bananas with vanilla wafers in large bowl.
Pour pudding mixture over wafers and bananas and then chill.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Combine all ingredients (except ginger ale).
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Pour into punch bowl over block of ice. (Note:
This punch will be a golden color.
An ice block can easily be made by using a round ring mold and adding a few maraschino cherries for color.)
Serves 150.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts and lay in pan.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Pour over chicken and cover pan with foil. Bake 2 hours or until done at 350°.

title: yummy chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together. Add the chocolate chips. Roll dough into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or tops crack.

title: old-fashioned sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, one by one.
Stir
soda
into
flour
or
sift
together.
To the creamed mixture,
add
the
flour and sour cream alternately. Begin and end with flour.
Beat the egg whites with the mixer until
stiff. Fold them carefully into the batter.
Pour into a Bundt
or
angel food
cake
pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruity pudding
directions: Make lemon pudding according to directions on package.
Add fruit cocktail.
Chill 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's favorite dinner
directions: Take all ingredients and go to favorite restaurant.

title: old fashioned dumpling pot pie
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, lard, salt and milk together to make a dough.
On wax paper or Reynolds Wrap, roll out dough.
Cut into squares.
Cook meat and broth.
When done, drop squares in, one at a time.
Cook until done.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine slightly beaten egg with milk and oil.
Add flour and salt, beat until moistened.
Dip sliced onion in batter and drain off excess batter; deep fry and drain off excess oil.

title: temptation
directions: Mix mutton, ketchup, spring onions, salt and pepper.
Cut bread into triangles, apply butter and spread mutton mixture on bread on two, like a triangle sandwich.

title: chocolate sundae sauce
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate in butter.
Add sugar and milk; cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Sauce thickens as it cools.
Make the day being used.

title: "camelot"(cam likes it a lot)
directions: Heat chicken broth to boil in medium saucepan.
Add can full of rice, cover and remove from heat.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring half and half and cream just to simmer in heavy medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Place chocolate chips in large bowl.
Pour cream mixture over; stir until chocolate melts.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, egg, liqueur and vanilla; whisk until blended.
Add bread cubes; toss to mix well. Transfer to 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: victory dessert
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in warm milk.
Cool.
Fold marshmallow mixture into whipped topping.
Fold in your favorite fruits.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle crushed graham crackers on top.
Chill.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Mix and bake in covered baking dish until rice is well done (about 60 minutes) at 350°.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
May prepare ahead of time and refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: cherry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in crushed crackers, nuts and vanilla.

title: clam spread
directions: Combine clams, cream cheese, onions and parsley.
Add 2 tablespoons sour cream or enough to spread on crackers.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit salad bowl(sugar-free)
directions: Place juice in bowl. Chop or slice unpeeled apple into juice to prevent darkening.
Peel peach and cut into small chunks.
Add to juice mixture.
Add remaining fruits and gently combine. Refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with mint or strawberries.

title: reese's peanut butter cake
directions: Heat until bubbling the margarine, water, eggs, cocoa and buttermilk.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla while hot but not on stove.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix peanut butter with oil.
Stir well.
Spread over cake.

title: french toast
directions: Beat ingredients in shallow bowl.
Dip slices of bread into egg mixture, turning to coat.
Fry bread on griddle until golden brown.
Flip and cook on other side the same way.
Top with fruit, confectioners sugar or syrup.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Heat skillet or wok for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add wine, boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Reduce to medium heat.
Add butter and melt.
Stir in soy sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook until combined, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl for later use.
Dip chicken pieces into sauce.
Place chicken into pan or wok (with a little sauce to keep moist) and cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add onions at this time and cook to likeness.
Stuff tortillas and wrap.
Serve with sour cream, olives, salsa, lettuce, cheese and guacamole.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend in flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in eggs and milk.
Blend well.
Cover.
Microwave on Power level 7 for 12 to 15 minutes.
When done, center will be barely set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
You may add 3/4 cup butter flavored cracker crumbs sprinkled over the top before baking.

title: pina colada
directions: Mix thoroughly in blender.
Serve in stemmed glasses.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Put in refrigerator 1 hour or more.
Form into walnut size balls.
Dip in sugar and place sugar side down on cookie sheet about 3-inches apart.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Boil together the milk and flour until thick.
Let cool until cold.
Beat together the sugar, butter, vanilla and shortening until whipped.
Add milk and flour; whip.

title: vege-pasta
directions: Prepare macaroni per package instructions.
Add vegetables during last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; cook over low heat, stirring often, until cheese is melted.
Add macaroni mixture; heat while stirring occasionally. Serves 4 to 6.

title: scallop stir-fry
directions: Reserve seasoning packet from noodles.
Cook and drain noodles as directed on package.
While noodles are cooking, heat olive oil in 12-inch skillet over high heat.
Add asparagus, bell pepper, onion and garlic; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add scallops; stir-fry until white. Mix contents of reserved seasoning packet, the soy sauce, lemon juice, sesame oil and pepper sauce; stir into scallop mixture. Stir in noodles; heat through.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Combine sugar, Kool-Aid and water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and add pineapple and orange juice.
Freeze in gallon or quart Ziploc bags.
When ready to use let unthaw until in icy form.

title: creamy baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Pour off drippings.
Pour 1/2 soup in casserole dish.
Place pork chops in dish and cover with remaining soup.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until tender.

title: summertime fried tomatoes
directions: Dip tomato slices in seasoned flour.
Cook in butter over low heat until lightly brown on both sides.
Remove to heated platter. Stir soup and milk into skillet.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Pour sauce over tomatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop vegetables fine.
Add rest of ingredients and cook all together, stirring frequently, for 2 1/4 hours or until thick. Seal in sterilized pint jars.

title: gotabki(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Scald cabbage in boiling water to soften leaves.
Remove one at a time; set aside.
Saute onion.
Cook rice until done.
Add onion to rice.
Add seasonings to meat; mix together with 1/2 soup.
Fill each cabbage leaf with mixture.
Put in roasting pan, side by side.
Pour tomatoes over cabbage.
Add remaining tomato soup.
Add pieces of salt pork.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry mixture, stirring just enough to make batter moist.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes in pans.
Freezes well.

title: english toffee
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and cook until brown, at least 10 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent burning. Pour into buttered pan or platter and lay chocolate on top, spreading when melted. Sprinkle nuts on top. Cool and break into pieces.

title: extra light mashed potatoes
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart size mixing bowl, dissolve water, Butter Buds and creamer; add potatoes.
Using an electric hand mixer, mix on whip speed until fluffy.

title: prehistoric pudding
directions: Crush cookies in food processor in Ziploc bag; roll out.
Pour milk into large bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon into each cup and fill 3/4 full with pudding mixture; top with the rest of crushed cookies.
Let stand an hour in cold place.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line an 11 x 16-inch pan with foil and place in the crackers. Put sugar and butter in boiler and boil for 3 minutes.
Then pour over crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes or until the crackers float.
Take out and put chocolate chips all over.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Snap
off
tough
ends of asparagus. Remove scales from stalks with
a
knife
or vegetable peeler, if desired. Cover asparagus and
cook
in a small amount of water 6 to 8 minutes or
until asparagus is crisp-tender.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easter egg relish
directions: Drain pickled beets.
Grind up beets with food grinder.
Stir together beets and horseradish.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.
Best if made a day or two ahead.
Peel and slice Easter eggs.
Put a good tablespoon of relish on top.
Enjoy!

title: mom's pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and water.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Chill about 1 hour in refrigerator.
Form into rolls size of fingers.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw vegetables; combine with soup, sour cream and pepper in a shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove; top with cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix shortening and 1/2 cup brown sugar thoroughly.
Stir in 1 cup flour.
Flatten into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix both cheeses together.
Brown ground beef and onion. Layer in casserole dish, meat, cooked noodles, cheese, meat, noodles, cheese and jar of pizza sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked bluefish in perfection
directions: Split the fish down the back; wipe it well and lay in a greased baking dish.

Melt the butter and add salt, pepper, onion and lemon juice and pour a little of the mixture over the fish. Place in a hot oven (400°) and bake about 1/2 hour, basting with butter preparation every 10 minutes.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish. Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Drain. Stir in water, tomato sauce and paste as well as all spices.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and stir in thawed vegetables and all but 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Spoon into greased baking dish.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well before baking.

title: old-fashioned doughnuts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, mace and salt.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed or with spoon, beat eggs well; beat in shortening, sugar, then buttermilk.
Add flour mixture all at once; beat just until smooth.
Refrigerate 1 hour or longer.

title: cocktail smoky links
directions: Combine chili sauce and grape jelly in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly, 3 minutes or until begins to boil.
Add sausages; cook 3 more minutes or until heated.
Stir often.
Serve with wooden picks.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: walnut-raisin corn relish
directions: If using fresh corn, remove husks and silk. Cut enough kernels from corn to make 1 1/2 cups.
Dice onion and red pepper.
In 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook onion and red pepper until tender, about 10 minutes. Add corn, raisins, brown sugar, vinegar, salt and 1/2 cup water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes or until corn is tender. Remove saucepan from heat. Stir in chopped walnuts and parsley.
Cover and refrigerate if not serving right away.
Makes 2 1/2 cups relish.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Warm soup in medium saucepan to smooth consistency; add milk and stir until creamy.
(Don't add milk to cold soup.)
Season to taste.
Add green beans and fold in with rubber spatula so beans don't break.
Place into a medium size casserole dish; sprinkle cheese on top and cover with fried onions.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve immediately; it loses it's appeal overnight.

title: hot sauce
directions: Drain juice from tomatoes and 1 can of Ro-Tel.
Put all tomatoes, salt and garlic powder in blender.
Blend short time; don't want it too fine.

title: aunt bessie's corn relish
directions: Cook corn-on-the-cob for 2 minutes.
Drain and cool slightly and cut from the cob.
Combine with chopped peppers, celery, onions, vinegar and seasoning; bring to a boil and simmer gently for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pack into 1/2 pint or 1 pint jars, filling to within 1/2-inch of the top.
Adjust lids and process in a hot water bath 5 minutes.
Remove from water bath and complete the seal.

title: spicy creamed corn(ready in 30 minutes or less.)
directions: In a saucepan, heat the cream cheese until melted. Add the corn, chilies, green onions and red pepper. Cook and stir until heated through.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Put chops in a large covered skillet and cover the top of meat with lemon, onion and pepper.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour the tomato juice over all and dot with butter.
Cover and cook on top of stove for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Lift on a hot platter, being careful to keep the rings in place.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge ice cream topping
directions: Mix first 8 items together.
Microwave 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Microwave again for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add peanut butter. Mix and serve.

title: spaghetti superb
directions: Lightly brown meat.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender. Add rest of ingredients except cheese.
Place in 3-quart casserole. Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serves 6 or 7. May be frozen.

title: potato and wiener casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp and hold for later.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Add soup, vinegar, salt, pepper and beans.
Heat.
Add potatoes and wieners.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes. Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.

title: m&m candy cookies
directions: Blend butter, peanut butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in M&M's candies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: fruit soup
directions: Cover dried fruit with water (any combination of raisins, prunes or apricots).
Boil slowly for 20 minutes.
Add brown sugar to taste.
Thicken, if desired, with cornstarch dissolved in 1/3 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Some like to add pearl (big) cooked tapioca instead of cornstarch.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Brown beef, sausage, onions and pepper in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain, add pizza sauce, mushrooms and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat. Mix macaroni and milk in a bowl.
Layer ground beef mixture, macaroni, cheese and pepperoni, half at a time in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marty's appetizer
directions: Allow cream cheese to reach room temperature (75°).
Boil asparagus until 2/3 done (allow to remain stiff), then allow to cool.
Once cool, roll asparagus in room temperature cream cheese, then wrap with piece of Prosciutto.
Pin with toothpick and serve.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, water, cheese and sherry.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir now and then.
Add turkey, pimientos, parsley and cooked vermicelli or spaghetti.
Heat.
Serves 4.

title: belgium red cabbage
directions: Slice red cabbage.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook covered until cabbage is done.
Serve hot.
Goes great with chicken and pork.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Place roast in deep baking dish. Place potatoes and carrots around it.
Slice onion on top of roast.
Pour mushroom soup over this.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 375°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine milk, butter, cocoa and sugar.
Bring to rolling boil. Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter, coconut, vanilla flavoring and oats.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and let cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: In hot bacon grease, cook 1 1/2 cups rice until golden brown. Add the garlic powder, cumin seed, pepper, bell pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour all this into 3 cups salted, boiling water.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; leave covered and let steam for 15 minutes prior to serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: southern bread pudding
directions: Mix together well.
Place in shallow 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream, lemon sauce or vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of deep dish with 1 pie crust.
Combine all other ingredients (except crust) in a large bowl; pour into deep dish.
Top the mixture with the second crust.
Crimp edges and punch with a fork.
Bake in an oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: simple supper
directions: Brown 1 pound hamburger and drain.
In a 9-inch square glass pan, combine can of soup, peas, hamburger, onion, salt and pepper. Spread evenly in pan.
Then sprinkle the cheese over top.
Next place a single layer of Tater Tots (frozen) on top, covering the entire pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-fat brownie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick vegetable spray and set aside.
Place filling, water, egg whites and vanilla in a large bowl and mix well.

title: queen of hearts cherry tarts
directions: Thoroughly combine the flour, butter, cream cheese and sugar. Chill 2 hours.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
With a doughnut cutter, cut 24 rings.

Then remove the inner circle of the cutter or cut around the outer edge of the cutter and make 12 circles. Take 12 of the 24 rings and place one on each of the circles. Moisten the rings and place a second ring on each.
Press edges with fork.
Bake 7 minutes at 450°.
Cool.
Fill with pie filling or jam.
Serve.
Makes 12 tarts.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Soak cabbage in cold salt water for 1 hour.
Boil in sufficient salt water to cover until almost tender.
Drain. Remove center, leaving 2 layers of leaves.
Shred the portion of cabbage which was removed.
Add ham, crumbs, onions, parsley, egg, cooking fat and salt and pepper.
Pack lightly into cabbage shell. Tie leaves tightly to hold the stuffing in place.
Place in roaster.
Baste with oleo which has been combined with 1 cup water.
Bake in slow oven (350°) for about 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: e-z cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls into sugar. Put balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Saute onions and ground beef.
Add other ingredients and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Serve with noodles or cooked rice.

title: berry apple relish
directions: Mix well and chill at least 1 hour.

title: delicious cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in a double boiler and add tomatoes.
Mix together.
Serve with tortilla chips, corn chips or crackers.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Blend together cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and liquid smoke.
Add salmon.
Shape into a ball. Cover with topping.
Chill.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello, stirring until dissolved.
Add peanuts and pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Quickly form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: quick quiche
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients in blender and pour into a pie pan.
Gently put in the cheese and meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly browned and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating often after each addition.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and flour in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shredded pork tacos
directions: In medium skillet cook onion & garlic until soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in salsa & shredded pork. Heat for 10-15 minutes or until pork is thoroughly heated. Heat tortillas according to pkg. directions; keep heated tortillas covered until ready to use. Divide pork mixture onto tortillas. Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, cheese and sour cream, if desired.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and bell pepper.
Mix rice, water, soup, salt, pepper and bouillon cubes.
Add hamburger mixture.
Cook until rice is done at 350°.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water and cook together until clear, then set aside.
Add a bit of salt to egg whites and whip until foamy or standing in peaks at which time you add the mixture of cornstarch, slowly.
Continue beating until creamy, then add sugar gradually beating again until creamy.
Pile on pie and seal all edges.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° or until golden brown.
Does not weep or get watery.

title: italian spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add whole tomatoes, crushed, tomato paste, water, sugar and all the spices.
Form ground beef into 1-inch balls and add to sauce.
Simmer slow about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve meatball sauce over hot spaghetti.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired. Leftover sauce may be refrigerated for 2 days.

title: candy bar
directions: Mash bananas.
Add cereal and chocolate mix.
Mix well and add peanut butter.
Mix and shape into a bar.
Put in freezer for a little while before eating.
Makes 1 bar.
Double recipe for 2 bars.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and fry bacon.
Add everything together and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves. Serves 4.

title: classy potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together the cheese, sour, sour cream, milk and onions.
Set the soup mixture aside.
Crush corn flakes into coarse crumbs.
Coarsely shred the potatoes.
Immediately stir the potatoes into the soup mixture to prevent browning.
Spray oblong pan with no-stick spray. Transfer the potato mixture to the baking dish.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour or until the potatoes are tender.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and just before serving add mayonnaise (just enough to blend the ingredients to preferred consistency).
Sprinkle bacon bits on top (optional).

title: night-before breakfast
directions: Stir juice from 1/2 lemon and 2 tablespoons of oil into a large pot of salted, boiling water.
Add artichokes and boil for 5 minutes or until almost tender.
Remove artichokes and cool under cold running water.
Reserve artichoke cooking water.
Peel outer leaves from 8 artichokes down to tenderest part (leave 4 artichokes with leaves intact); cut off stem.
Cut peeled artichokes into bite size pieces (about 1 1/2 inches long); set aside.

title: orange cream torte
directions: Combine egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, orange juice, orange rind and lemon extract; beat until mixture is thick and lemon colored.
Beat whites until frothy.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; beat until rounded peaks form.
Spread yolk mixture over egg whites; fold together.
Fold in cake flour, sifting 1/4 cup at a time.
Turn into 2 (9-inch) pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; invert, then loosen with spatula.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into balls.
Bake at 350°
until done.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in 1 teaspoon oil.
In a separate pan, brown onion in 1 teaspoon oil.
When onion is browned, add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, chili powder and garlic powder.
Stir well. Drain and mash 1 quart of tomatoes and add to mixture along with beef and beans.
Simmer on low heat for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meal in one muffins
directions: Grease large muffin tin (Texas size).
Combine corn meal, flour and baking powder; set aside.
Whisk together eggs, sour cream, oil, mustard and chives.
Stir in ham and cheese.
Mix in dry ingredients just until moistened.
Bake at 350° until golden. Remove while hot!
Yields 6 large muffins!

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour, then mix in milk and eggs.
Beat well and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla last.
Pour into baked pie shells and top with meringue.

title: pizza
directions: Mexs flower and oil to gather and flat it owt.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Top each tomato with last 4 ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then 10 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together everything except dressing mix.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and sugar. Pour in dissolved yeast.
Work in Crisco with pastry knife or 2 knives.
Mix in buttermilk.
Pour batter onto floured surface. Roll 1/2 inch thick; cut into circles.
Fold circles in half and put on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: waffles (our select recipe)
directions: This recipe makes 60 waffles.
If you want only 30, just cut recipe in half.
The batter should be smooth and about the consistency of thick cream.
Heat the waffle iron by dipping it into heated Crisco Shortening for about 10 seconds.
Remove it and dip it into the batter, absolutely to the top.
Then dip into pan containing enough Crisco to cover the top of the iron.
As soon as batter starts to expand from the iron, gradually lift it up until waffle drops off by itself.
If batter sticks to waffle iron and browns too rapidly, this shows that the Crisco is too hot.

title: ritz cracker apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cream of tartar and water.
Let come to boil.
Drop in Ritz crackers.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Cook 1 more minute. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook until pie shell is done.
Can't tell it from apple pie.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; beat 5 minutes.
Add baking powder 1/2 cup flour and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup sugar melted to which has been added boiling water and cooked to a syrup.
Fold in slowly.
Bake in 2 layers in 350° oven.
Frost with caramel or favorite frosting.

title: david's favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In pot, add small amount of milk and cheese.
Add macaroni to cheese and milk.
Heat through until cheese is melted.
Season to taste.

title: frankly good spaghetti
directions: In skillet, brown hot dogs and cook onions in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally. Makes 5 cups.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring apricot nectar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature, then add apricots, buttermilk and preserves.
Stir in Cool Whip and chill.

title: tomato jam
directions: Peel, core and chop tomatoes.
In heavy pot bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Measure tomato mix, you need 3 cups.
Put in large pot and add lemon juice, lemon rind and sugar.
Mix well; bring to a full boil over high heat.
Then boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in Certo immediately.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Continue stirring and skimming about 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Ladle in sterilized jars and seal at once with paraffin.
Makes 29 medium jars.

title: pear cheese salad
directions: Mix gelatin and cream cheese together.
Add boiling water. Blend with rotary mixer. Chill until thickened. Beat pears with rotary beater. Add pears and nuts to gelatin mixture.
Chill again and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter together and let boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to set.

title: spiced ice tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags; cover and steep 5 minutes. Remove tea bags, squeezing gently. Stir in sugar, orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice and water. Chill and serve over ice. "Great beverage for tailgate parties!"
tags: regular size cinnamon-apple flavor tea bags

title: taco chicken wingettes
directions: Remove wing tips from chicken; discard.
Cut each wing at joint to make 2 sections.
Set aside.

title: chicken and roast peppers
directions: To roast peppers:
Cut peppers into quarters and core.
Place peppers under broiler in oven and let them blacken.
Take them out and put into sealed paper bag for 2 to 3 minutes.
They will be ready to peel easily.
Dredge chicken in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Saute garlic in oil until browned, then remove.
Fry chicken in garlic oil, turning to brown on all sides.
After frying chicken for 20 minutes, add wine, basil, salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add peppers and heat for 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: english trifle
directions: Break up pound cake and place in large glass bowl.
Prepare Jell-O as package directs, using reserved juice and sherry in place of cold water.
Pour Jell-O over pound cake.
Add strawberries.
Refrigerate and allow to set, preferably overnight. Prepare dessert mix as package directs and pour over Jell-O-pound cake mix.
Refrigerate and allow to set.
Whip cream and top dessert.

title: black bean, corn and bell pepper salad
directions: Drain beans and cover with fresh water.
Cook until tender. Cool beans and drain.
Combine beans, corn, green and red peppers, jalapeno peppers and onions and parsley.
Add olive oil and lime juice.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: guacamole
directions: In blender or food processor combine avocados, onion, peppers, garlic, lime juice and salt.
Blend until nearly smooth.
Transfer mixture to a bowl.
Cover and chill for up to 24 hours.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: hot stuffed peppers
directions: Wash and core hot peppers.
Mix sausage and stuff each pepper. Lay peppers in baking dish.
Pour enough spaghetti sauce to cover each pepper.
Add cheeses to cover peppers.
Cover with tinfoil and bake approximately 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spanish omelette
directions: Saute onions until tender, then add all remaining ingredients, except flour and water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken with flour, mixed to smooth paste with the water.
Remove bay leaf and cloves.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Makes three 8-inch pies.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: chicken risotto
directions: In large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter and brown chicken pieces over medium heat.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add remaining butter, rice and garlic to skillet and cook, stirring constantly, until rice is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add onion; continue cooking, stirring occasionally, about 2 minutes. Stir in chicken broth and basil.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Gently stir in chicken and simmer until chicken is heated through and rice is tender, about 5 minutes. Top with cheese and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together, put in a buttered baking dish.

title: tammy's brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Pour oil, eggs, vanilla and pre-melted chocolate in center.
Stir together; stir in chips.
Pour into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bacon dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 3 pieces.
Cut bacon into 3 pieces.
Wrap bacon around hot dog and secure with toothpick.
Sprinkle brown sugar on each layer as you place them in a casserole pan.
Bake for no more than 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Share and enjoy. Yields 10 servings.

title: italian spinach and eggs
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Mix together with cooked, chopped spinach and beaten eggs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Peel skin and put in mixer bowl.
Mash with potato masher.
Add butter, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Mix until fluffy.
Put in souffle dish.
Place marshmallows on top and heat at 250° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn heat up last 5 minutes to brown marshmallows.

title: lasagna(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Brown meat slowly; drain off excess fat.
Add bay leaf, garlic, basil, salt, mushrooms, tomatoes and tomato paste to meat and simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Heat oven
Grease bottom and sides of 10 x 10 x 2-inch
ceramic
baking
dish.
Spread
the chocolate chips evenly over
the bottom of the dish.
Pour the chocolate syrup over the chocolate chips.
Combine hot water, oil and egg in a mixing bowl. Add
brownie
mix and cinnamon.
Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Spread over
chips
and syrup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Servings must be spooned out because product is too rich and
gooey
to slice.
Serve
either cool or warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: grandma's macaroni and cheese
directions: This is not an exact recipe. It is adjustable to what you like!

title: linguini salad
directions: Note:
The quantities for the vegetables do not have to be exact.
Vegetable quantities can be according to one's own taste.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick melted margarine and egg together.
Cook in sheet pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with marshmallows.
Return to oven until melted.

title: georgia caviar
directions: Soak peas in water overnight.
Drain peas and place in large saucepan.
Add enough water to cover peas.
Bring to a boil; reduce to simmer and cook 40 minutes over medium heat.
Drain water from peas.
Pour Italian dressing over peas; add remaining ingredients except chips and cool.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Serve at room temperature with tortilla chips.
Yields 7 cups.

title: peaches au st. croix
directions: Put peach slices in a jar and add enough peach syrup to cover peaches.
Add rum extract to peaches and stir gently to blend. Cover jar and refrigerate 24-48 hours.
Combine sour cream and brown sugar.
Drain peaches and spoon into serving dishes.
Spoon sweetened sour cream over peaches and top with nuts.
Serves 4.

title: cheddar spoon bread
directions: Scald 1 1/2 cups milk.
Mix cornmeal with remaining cold milk and add to hot milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until thickened, approximately 5 minutes.
Add cheese, butter, sugar and salt; stir in eggs.
Pour into 1-quart greased baking dish; bake at 350° for about 35 minutes, or until lightly browned and set.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: brioche couronne
directions: Put ingredients in order given into bread baker (1 or 1 1/2 pound loaf size).
Save the single yolk for glaze.
Set bread baker on dough cycle.
When cycle is complete, shape dough.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Layer the broccoli and chicken. Pour sauce over the broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle cheese over that. Put bread crumbs over all and pour margarine overall. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt margaret's cooked dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a small saucepan.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 to 1/2 cup butter.
Stir into mixture.
The dressing gets thicker as it cools.
Makes about 1/2 pint of dressing.
Excellent for potato salad.

title: kati's almond joy cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions for 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bring 1 cup evaporated milk and 1 cup sugar to boil in saucepan.
Stir in marshmallows until melted.
Add coconut. Pour mixture over warm cake.
Bring 1/2 cup evaporated milk and 1 1/2 cups sugar to a boil.
Stir in margarine and chocolate chips until melted.
Add almonds.
Pour over coconut layer evenly. Enjoy!!!

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Trim meat from bones.
Add to soup.
Stir in noodles.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.

title: christmas bread(julekake)
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup of the warm milk.
Mix remaining milk, sugar, salt and cardamon; add softened yeast and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and melted butter and mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time and beat after each addition.
Add floured fruit.
Knead dough on a floured board.
Place in a large greased bowl and grease top of dough.
Let rise to double in volume.
Punch down and let rise a second time.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased baking dish. Cover with topping.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Stir in pineapple, 1 cup of nuts and other ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into ball and cover with the rest of the nuts.
Serve chilled.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Drain well.
Mash and mix with bread crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.
Form into balls and roll in corn meal.
Deep fry in oil until brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach well and squeeze out water. Stir in sour cream, mayonnaise, chopped onion, chestnuts and the soup mix. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: lima bean loaf
directions: Cook lima beans until tender and mash.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Form the mixture into a loaf and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
This recipe makes 6 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir into shortening mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts. Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes, until lightly browned, but still soft.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with wrinkled tops.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Spray glass baking dish with Pam.
Layer ingredients.
Layer squash, onion, saltines and cheese to make about 2 layers.
Mix together milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Cook cranberries in 1/2 cup water until popped open.
Combine jello, sugar, cranberries and pecans.
Pour into mold or 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish. Put in refrigerator until set.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
If desired, sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Blend ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with poultry or grilled fish.

title: "lighten" cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add oil, egg and lukewarm water; mix well.
Cover and set in a warm place for about 2 hours.
Pour into a well-greased, high sided pan and allow to rise for 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cranberry sauce for ham
directions: Mix all together and cook on High in microwave 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Cover and let stand.
Serve on ham.

title: creme puff dessert
directions: Heat butter and water together to boiling.
Remove from heat. Mix flour to form a ball.
Add eggs and mix with a beater until smooth.
Spread this in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Cool completely.

title: hush puppies #1
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add well beaten eggs and milk. Stir as little as possible.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until squash is tender. Drain well and mash; set aside.

title: bobby's spicy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash with butter and milk.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Serve.

title: pumpkin cake roll(yields 8 large slices)
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold into batter.
Line a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper and grease the paper.
Spread batter evenly in pan. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, until cake tests done when toothpick is inserted.
Turn onto towel which has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Remove paper.
Starting at narrow end, roll up cake and towel together.
Cool; unroll.
Spread with cream cheese filling; roll up again.
Chill or freeze, wrapped in foil, until ready to use. Cut in slices.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine cornbread mix, egg and milk.
Cook until done.
Cut up tomatoes, pepper, onion and bacon.
Combine in big bowl.
Add crumbled cornbread, mayonnaise and pickles (I substitute sweet pickle relish).
Put in refrigerator.
Better if it sets awhile.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain well.
Combine all ingredients.
Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Freeze.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 40 spinach balls.
Serve with breakfast or brunch or as hors d'oeuvres.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature, then mix salad dressing and cream cheese together well.
Spread a thin amount of mixture into each slice of ham.
Place 5 olives in a straight line lengthwise on narrow end of ham slices.
Very carefully begin to roll ham over the olives.
Roll as tightly as possible. Refrigerate 3 to 5 hours before slicing using a very sharp knife. Make each appetizer, about 1/4-inch thick.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans for several hours or overnight.
Cover with water; cook with ham bone, onion, bell pepper, celery, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook beans until tender, then add sausage that has been fried and drained.
Cook beans until done.

title: microwave chocolate ice crispy pie
directions: Mix chocolate syrup and chocolate chips in medium glass bowl. Microwave on High for 45 seconds or until hot; stir until smooth. Reserve 1/4 cup mixture.
Combine remaining chocolate mixture with cereal in bowl, stirring to coat well.
Press over bottom and side of buttered 8-inch pie plate with back of spoon.
Freeze for 15 to 20 minutes or until firm.
Mix reserved chocolate mixture with sour cream in bowl.
Spoon half the ice cream into pie shell.
Drizzle with half the sour cream mixture.
Repeat layers.
Freeze until serving time.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash pickles.
Place in brine (strong enough to hold up an egg) and leave for 5 days.
Remove from brine.
Wash and slice pickles 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with water and alum.
Let stand overnight.

title: aunt susan's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Add flour and lemon flavoring and knead.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Wash and clean raw vegetables.
Put in large kettle covered with water 3/4 full.
Cook until tender.
Saute meat and onion until onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add to cooked vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add about half jar of beef soup base.
Simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in large skillet.
Remove bacon to drain on paper towel.
Saute onions in hot bacon grease for about 3 minutes.
Add sliced okra and cook, stirring occasionally, until most of the ropiness is gone, 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes.
If necessary, add a little tomato juice or water while simmering.
Ten minutes before done, crumble bacon into mixture and finish cooking, covered.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Boil noodles. Drain and cool.
Mix oil, lemon juice and m.s.g. in a jar.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Mix vegetables, noodles, marinade and mayo.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet and cook 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Beat eggs with spices.
Add oatmeal and Melba toast and stir.
Add meat; mix well.
Make meatballs and brown in skillet.
Put meatballs into large saucepan and cook in water (slightly over top of meatballs) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with gravy, noodles or rice.

title: easy cheese dip
directions: Mix both ingredients in food processor or blender until smooth.
Serve with Dutch-style pretzels, Pinah's garlic chips or breadsticks.

title: no peek stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a dutch oven or other oven-proof pan.
There is no need to brown the meat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 4 - 4-1/2 hours, covered.
DO NOT OPEN THE LID DURING COOKING TIME.
tags: cream of mushroom soup and equal amt. of water

title: snowballs
directions: Blend together dates, walnuts and peanut butter.
Shape into small balls about 1-inch diameter.
Make a thin icing with the confectioners sugar and cream.
Roll ball in icing and then in flaked coconut.
Let stand until the icing is set.
May be served after chilling or place in covered dish and stored in the refrigerator.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Place wings in a single layer in baking pan.
Combine vinegar, sugar, catsup, flour, celery salt, cloves and mustard in a saucepan and bring to a boil; simmer until smooth.
Pour over wings.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cover with tinfoil first 20 minutes.

title: bean pot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Combine all ingredients into large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Then add flour, vanilla, apples and nuts.
Mix together.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and crumble.
Butter slices of bread and cube. Grate sharp cheese.
Beat eggs well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Line bottom with bread cubes.
Sprinkle sausage over the bread.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over sausage.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Uncover the last few minutes for browning.

title: caramel apples(delicious with pork)
directions: Cut apples in half, leaving hole in center.
Place in glass baking dish, hole side up.
Make sauce by mixing together the sugars, flour, butter and vanilla.
Add enough water to make a thick paste.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender.
Baste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook until berries pop open.
Add sugar, Jell-O, pineapple and chopped pecans and let set overnight in flat pan or bowl.
Mix chopped cream cheese, marshmallows and Cool Whip or cream.
Whip and spread over cranberry mixture.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain 3 cans of vegetables and place in bowl.
To them add onion, celery and green pepper.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve with raw veggies.

title: doe-doe's vegetable dip
directions: Melt bouillon cube in two tablespoons hot water.
Mix all ingredients together with a mixer.
Serve with your favorite fresh vegetables.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out pizza dough into rectangle.
Place layer of meat, cheese and meat again on top, leaving about 1/2-inch border of dough.
Roll up lengthwise and tuck seams under bottom.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Bake on a pan in 375° oven until golden, 15 to 20 minutes, depending on oven.
Yields 1 large stromboli.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add chopped onion and cook until soft.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Add water to desired consistency.
Simmer several hours in crock-pot.
Serve over broken flour tortillas.
Add grated cheese on top.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and nuts.
Pour batter into well-greased (not floured) 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Grease large pan or Pyrex dish.
Line with 6 tortillas.
Add beef, which has been browned, with onions and seasoned with chili powder, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add beans with juice.
Lay sliced cheese on top.
Cover with remaining tortillas.
Top with mixture of Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken soup which has been heated. Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: party meat balls
directions: Make meatballs from first four ingredients and place in large (14 x 9) baking dish.

title: chicken enchilda casserolesante fe, new mexico
directions: Cook whole chicken.
Let cool.
Debone and shred chicken into strips.
Save chicken broth.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cool cake as directed on box.
Use wooden spoon handle to punch holes in cake while warm.
Mix 1 cup warm water with jello and pour over cake.
Pour strawberries over that and top with Cool Whip.

title: nancy's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into meatballs.
Brown in oil. Serve with favorite sauce with toothpicks.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Add milk to which the soda has been dissolved.
Mix.
Knead dough lightly.
Roll and cut out biscuits.
Put in greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 425°.

title: rice and chicken salad
directions: Mix salad dressing with oil and vinegar as package directions; leave out water. Marinate all vegetables in salad dressing. Cook rice; cool. Combine rice, chicken and mayonnaise; refrigerate. This can all be done the day before serving. Combine a few hours before serving.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, sugar and raisins.
Add buttermilk, all at once.
Mix with fork.
Knead dough, using 1/4 cup flour.
Make a large ball.
Cut an "X" on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in an iron skillet.
Rub butter on top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Top with Lemon Curd.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Put in crock-pot, add cheese chunks and stir.
Add chili beans and cook for several hours.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients well; add 5 small diced apples and 1 cup nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
May add caramel icing, if desired.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and cook on medium-low heat, stirring often, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding.
Garnish with sliced bananas and cookies.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Flatten chicken with mallet.
Whip together egg and oil in shallow dish.
Dip chicken into egg mixture then into bread crumbs.
Place chicken in shallow, nonstick baking dish.

title: jiffy dessert #1
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Pour in undrained fruit.
Make batter of remaining ingredients and pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix meal, flour, baking powder, milk, sugar and egg together. It will be lumpy.
Mix a little water at a time to get consistency you want.
Drop in deep fat and fry.

title: spicy potatoes
directions: Line cookie sheet(s) with foil.
Spray foil with nonstick vegetable spray.
Scrub potatoes and cut into spears (about 1/2-inch).
Place in single layer on foil.
Drizzle butter over potatoes, then sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cover potatoes with foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Spread beans in an 8 x 8-inch pan or on a platter.
Blend sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Layer on top of beans.
Top with shredded Cheddar and any other desired toppings. Serve cold or warm.

title: coconut dream bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread it in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Makes about 2 dozen.
This is awful rich.

title: taco sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chicken-turkey pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken or turkey and frozen vegetables.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: angel food deluxe cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Use a 10 x 4-inch ungreased tube pan.
Stir flour and first amount of sugar (confectioners) together to blend. Measure egg whites, cream of tartar and salt into large mixing bowl.
Beat until foamy.
Gradually add second amount of sugar (granulated).
Continue beating until meringue holds stiff peaks. Fold in gently only until the flour and sugar mixture disappears. Push batter into tube pan and gently cut through batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Invert on a funnel.
Let hang until cold.

title: thanksgiving dressing
directions: Mix bread, celery, margarine, spices and chicken livers.
Add water and mix.
Beat eggs and dry milk.
Add to bread mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 15 minutes.
Continue baking.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250, spray pan with non-stick spray.
Cut candy into small pieces.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk, cream margarine and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour.
Add remaining flour to buttermilk.
Add nuts, candy, dates, and coconut to batter.
Bake in tube pan 2 1/2 hours.

title: vegetarian lasagne
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl until well-blended. Cover bottom of large (15 x 10-inch) baking dish with thin layer of sauce.
Place a layer of uncooked noodles covering bottom (I use 6).
Put 1/2 of Ricotta mixture next.
Cover with sauce, sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Repeat with noodles, Ricotta, sauce and cheeses, then place one more noodle layer and top with more sauce.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for at least 1 1/2 hours or until noodles are tender.

title: sweet and sour turkey
directions: Drain peaches; reserve syrup.
Set aside.
In large skillet, saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil, about 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Mix well syrup, soy, vinegar, brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vegetables.
Cook and stir until thickened. Stir in turkey and peaches.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: spinach appetizer
directions: Melt margarine in a 5 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and serve.
Good slightly warm.

title: cherry broccoli flower salad
directions: Mix washed, dried, and prepared veggies with Italian dressing. Toss and serve chilled.

title: olive balls
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Add other ingredients, except olives.
Add enough mixture around olive to cover.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place gelatin and hot water in blender jar and blend a few seconds to dissolve gelatin.
Add the fruit, sugar and salt. Blend until fruits are finely chopped.
Add the pecans and blend just until mixed.
Don't overblend or you will have too much liquid and not a firm jello mold.

title: vegetarian yok soba
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Stir-fry vegetables in 1 tablespoon oil until crisp and tender, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Season with soy sauce and cayenne pepper.
Add the cooked and drained spaghetti to skillet. Stir, mixing with vegetables.
Add 1/2 cup ketchup.
Heat until spaghetti is hot.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Season to taste.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve hot on buns.

title: pecan squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in casserole first.
Steam squash with onion until tender.
Drain and mash thoroughly.
Add other ingredients to mashed squash, then put in casserole on top of butter.

title: baked brie
directions: Wrap Brie with rolls - completely cover and overlap - smooth dough and bake in 350° oven until golden brown (about 15-20 minutes).

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour pie filling and pineapple; blend slightly.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit mixture and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 12 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles(cold process)
directions: Pack cucumbers into a gallon jar (preferably large mouth jar). Mix other ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Cover, but do not seal.
Keep in refrigerator.
Pickles become real crisp.
Shake jar frequently to mix ingredients.
Ready to use after setting 2 weeks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown in 1 stick margarine, 1/2 cup chopped onions and 1/2 cup chopped green pepper.
Add 2 cans cream of mushroom soup, almonds, pimento and mushrooms.
Mix and add 4 cups cooked chicken and 1 box wild rice, cooked.
Place in greased 3-quart casserole and top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cindy's doodles
directions: Tear rolls into 16 pieces.
Take one and flatten it out and place a peanut butter cup on it.
Pull dough up around the cup and pinch the dough together.
Dip into melted butter and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, pinched side down. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake according to the directions on the crescent roll tube.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Serve topped with grated cheese or sour cream.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Cook sausage (out of casing) with pepper and onion; drain fat. Add mushrooms.
Add Prego sauce and spices; simmer.
Boil ziti. Drain ziti and add to sauce.
Continue simmering to blend flavors.
Serve.

title: kids' kasserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add sugar and tomato sauce; simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, green onion and cheese.
Layer noodles, beef and cheese mixture.
Top with another 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange icy delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ice cream freezer. Let run until the ice cream is hard.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased baking dish. Put 1/4 to 1/2 cup more ketchup on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
If possible, allow sauce to stand overnight to blend flavors before using.
This is enough sauce for 3 small broilers, split in half.
This recipe makes 6 servings.

title: lime-seared grilled whitefish(with mango salsa)
directions: Mix the spices and sprinkle onto only one side of the fish. Squeeze 1 lime over fish, and grill over medium coals until fish is flakey. Garnish with mango salsa.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Cook in electric skillet until smooth gravy.
Simmer meatballs in gravy.
Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Cream well together the Crisco and sugar. Beat in egg yolks. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and add alternately with orange juice and water. Add orange rind. Fold in egg whites. Pour into 2 (9-inch) lined round pans. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cool on wire rack in the pans about 10 minutes. Turn out and allow to cool completely before filling and frosting.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water slightly; mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Mix together, then mix nuts in mixture until well coated.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°. Loosen with spatula immediately; let cool.

title: pepperoni potatoes
directions: In a large non stick skillet, melt butter.
Cook potatoes and onion on low heat until tender (about 20 minutes).
Salt and pepper to taste.
When potatoes are done, top with tomato sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Cover and cook on low heat until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: kraut buns
directions: Mix hot roll mix according to directions.
While that's rising, cook cabbage, onion, celery and meat in heavy skillet in small amount of oil, until done.
Drain well.
Roll the hot roll mixture on floured surface to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 4-inch squares.

title: instant clam dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream and drained clams.
Add part of the leek soup to taste (usually 1/4 cup).
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Grate carrots and raisins in food processor. combine other ingredients. Mix well. Refrigerate, 1 1/2 hrs before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, or until slightly bubbly.

title: apple pie(so easy and sooo good!)
directions: Heat margarine in skillet.
Brown apple in melted margarine with brown sugar and apple pie spice.
Stuff into pita bread. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or microwave on High for 1 minute. Serves 1.
Each serving equals 1 fat, 1 fruit, 3 extras and 1 bread.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a very large bowl or punch bowl, layer the ingredients as follows:
1/2 of sheet cake, sliced into chunks.
Cover with 1/2 of can of crushed pineapple with juice.
1/2 of can of cherry pie filling.
1/2 of vanilla pudding.
1/2 of whipped topping.
Begin again at step 1 and layer with the other 1/2 of each ingredient.
Top with crushed nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mountain chow chow
directions: Chop cabbage real fine.
Chop tomatoes and peppers real fine too, then mix with cabbage.
Add salt and mix.
Pack in stone jar or crock and mash down tight so brine will rise over top of the mixture.
Cover with a cloth or a tight cover and let set until it works, then skim the top of any scum and put in sterilized jars and process in water bath 15 minutes.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk and evaporated milk.
Add 2 orange drinks and mix well.
Add pineapple and mix well.
Pour into 5-quart freezer bucket. Add orange drinks until freezer is 2/3 full.
Freeze as any ice cream. Pack down after freezing for about 15 minutes before serving.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.
Mixture keeps in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, all sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup morsels.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: cheese, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Pour 1 1/3 cups of boiling water over the frozen broccoli and break it apart.
Mix the rice in.
Mix cheese, soup, onion and celery in a deep bowl; pour into the rice-broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweepstakes prize cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream and bananas.
Mix separately, frosting mix, butter and oats.
Alternate mixtures in layers in tube pan, ending with crumb mixture.
Bake 50 minutes or until done in 300° oven.

title: lucy's tuna casserole(fast and easy)
directions: Crush potato chips.
Mix water and soup together until smooth. In a baking dish, place crumbled tuna and chips in layers.
Pour soup mixture over layers.
Stick knife into bowl in about 4 places for soup to drain into a little.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Pour cake into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs and pumpkin together and spoon over cake dough.
Then pour 1/2 cup boiling water over this.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 1/2 to 3 tablespoons per cup.

title: super chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add egg and cocoa liquid. Mix soda and boiling water.
Add this, flour and baking powder, mix well.
Pour into greased 9 inch square pan.
The batter will be thin.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
This cake doubles well.
Bake in a 9 X 13 inch pan or a bundt pan for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a large stockpot, cook the bacon until almost done.
Add the onions and garlic.
Cook until the onions are tender.
Add the diced tomatoes and about 4 cups water.
Slowly, add about half of the tomato paste.
Season with salt and pepper and the beef bouillon cubes.
Slowly add the tomato paste.
(How much you use will be up to you.)
Add either fresh vegetables such as corn, celery, potatoes, carrots, zucchini, or if in a rush, add 2 cans Veg-All.
Finally add the ditalini and let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
This is even better served the next day.

title: quick sugar and cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat altogether with electric mixer on number 3 speed, about 2 minutes.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl while beating.
Pour batter into 8-inch square baking pan or a deep 9-inch layer cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and put on topping.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Poach mushroom caps in bouillon until slightly limp.
Chop mushroom stems.
Saute them in butter with onion until onion is transparent.
Put broccoli in one layer in oblong baking dish (8 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch).
Put mushroom caps over broccoli. Sprinkle mushroom stems and onion over mushroom caps.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake until bubbly (usually 20 to 30 minutes) in 350° oven.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cut chicken into small chunks.
Cook rotini noodles and drain. Dip broccoli and peas into boiling water for a few minutes, until cooked slightly, but still crunchy.
Mix chicken, noodles and vegetables together in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with dry salad seasoning mix and Parmesan cheese and add a small amount of salad dressing.
Stir so that the spices and salad dressing coat the salad.
Chill before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Fill cavity with sausage. Replace stems.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with dressing and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook together until well blended sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and salt.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Cool. Store in refrigerator.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine tea, orange juice granules, sugar, cloves, cinnamon and allspice, mixing thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container.
Combine 2 or 3 teaspoons of mixture with 1 cup of hot water, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Yield: 5 1/2 cups.

title: italian fig cookies
directions: Soak figs and raisins in water overnight (cover fruit).
Drain and reserve liquid.
Put in food chopper or processor and chop. Transfer to kettle; add honey and juice and let cook for at least 1/2 hour.
Watch carefully and add some of the reserved juice if necessary.
Add almonds.
Roll out dough.
Starting at one end, put a line of figs about 1 1/2-inches; fold over and cut, then start another row.
Cut roll into squares of desired size.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Slash top of cooked cake while hot, then pour sweetened condensed milk over top and allow to cool.
Mix together whipped topping, pineapple and cream of coconut.
Frost cake with this mixture, then sprinkle with coconut.
Serve cold.

title: hell-fire crispy balls
directions: In medium bowl combine all 7 ingredients.
Stir in the egg, juice, onion and Tabasco.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, bring 1 inch oil to 350°.
Drop batter by teaspoons into oil, fry a few at a time, 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 dozen balls.

title: heaven on earth chocolate dessert
directions: Cook cake.
Cool; cut or break it up into bite-size pieces using one half of cake.
Make instant pudding.
In trifle bowl, put 1/2 cake and 1/2 pudding on top.
Put 1/2 Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Break frozen candy with meat mallet.
Sprinkle one candy bar on top of Cool Whip.
Repeat and make second layer (cake, pudding, Cool Whip and candy).
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours.

title: cheddar corn bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the corn bread mix, eggs, milk and yogurt until blended.
Stir in corn and cheese.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 22 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, celery and butter until clear.
Add everything but cheeses, spaghetti and cornstarch.
Cook until boiling.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into mixture.
Cook until thick.
Mix Parmesan cheese with spaghetti.
Layer chicken mix, spaghetti and cheese, ending with cheese on top in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in a 1-cup liquid measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead about 10 minutes. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch round (or smaller) cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve hot with butter, ham, honey, etc.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with sugar, vanilla, vinegar and eggs. Add coconut, nuts and raisins.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: reuben katie's mixed pickles
directions: Cook each vegetable separately with a little salt.
Put together;
add vinegar and
let stand overnight, then heat and can.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips in double boiler or microwave. Pour over marshmallows and nuts.
Divide into 3 parts and roll in waxed paper sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until you want to use, then just slice off.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine in boiling, lightly salted water until tender; rinse with hot water and drain.
Combine 2/3 cup whipping cream and 1/2 cup butter in pan large enough to hold fettuccine.
Cook until butter melts and mixture is thickened.
Add fettuccine to cream mixture.
Place over low heat and toss.
Add remaining cream, butter and cheese.
Toss; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve with added cheese.

title: thick and chewy pizza dough
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of water with yeast and sugar.
Let stand until bubbly, about 5 minutes.
Put flour, oil and salt in food processor and process about 5 seconds with steel blade.
Add yeast mixture and process until blended, about 10 seconds.
