Turn on processor and drizzle just enough water through feed tube so dough forms a ball that cleans the side of bowl.
Process so that the ball turns around about 25 times.
Put dough ball onto a 14-inch greased pizza pan or large cookie sheet.

title: sour cream apple cake
directions: Cut butter into dry cake mix with coconut.
Put in a pan. Bake for 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on top.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples slices.
Bake 35 minutes until slightly brown.
Spread sour cream on top and serve.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar, cinnamon and margarine for crust.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.

title: stuffed tomato cups
directions: In bowl, combine chicken, celery, pimiento, pecans and lime juice.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing to taste.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut tops off tomatoes; scoop out inside. Spoon chicken mixture into tomato cups.
Serve immediately.

title: tuna salad bake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Then fold in egg slices.
Pile lightly into casserole dish and sprinkle with crushed chips.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Pour into 2 (8-inch) unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry.
Trim and remove stems and chop. Dip outside of caps in salad oil and place in greased baking dish. Saute chopped stems and minced onion in butter.
Stir in bread crumbs, dill weed and Worcestershire.
Stuff caps with mixture and bake 15 minutes at 325°

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Add other ingredients, except nuts. Mix thoroughly.
Form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, crumbs, milk, onion, garlic, salt, Worcestershire sauce and egg.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cook in 400° oven in 9 x 13-inch baking dish 20 to 25 minutes.

title: awesome iced tea
directions: Place tea bags in pan. Add only enough water to cover bags and bring to a boil. Remove tea bags and add sugar. Add mix to 1 gallon of water. Stir in lemonade and chill.

title: "jake the great's" grilled franks
directions: Insert cheese in each split hot dog.
Angle wrap one slice bacon around each hot dog, securing with toothpicks.
Grill on medium heat until bacon is brown and crisp.
Serve with chili, baked beans and coleslaw.

title: meat casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake, covered, for 3 hours at 325°.
No extra salt needed.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add strawberries and pour in cooled pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable-bordered pasta bake
directions: Break pasta into 1-inch pieces.
Cook pasta according to package directions, then drain.
In a covered saucepan, cook broccoli, onion, green or sweet red peppers and garlic in a small amount of water about 10 minutes or until broccoli is crisp and tender; drain.

title: mrs. strickler's fastnachts
directions: About 4:00 p.m., start the following:
In a large (approximately 10-quart) pan, dissolve the yeast in one cup warm water.
Add 3 tablespoons flour, mashed potatoes and remaining two cups water, beating well after each addition.
Cover with tea towel and let sit in warm place.
About 8 or 9 o'clock, add the sugar, salt, melted Crisco and flour.
Work in the flour until dough is soft; it will be sticky.
Cover and let sit overnight in a warm place.

title: sherry cream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt chocolate and butter over hot water in a double boiler. Mix together and set aside to cool slightly. Beat eggs in a mixing bowl until light. Gradually cream in sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Beat 1 minute. Stir in chocolate mixture and pour into greased and floured 10 x 14-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes. Cool.

title: warm taco dip
directions: Saute onions, peppers and hamburg.
Add salsa.
Spread cream cheese in two 8 x 8-inch glass dishes.
Pour mixture of peppers, onions, hamburg and salsa over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Combine soup, chili peppers, 1/2 green onion, sour cream and 1/2 of cheeses.
Mix well.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups.
Add chicken to remainder.
Put 3 tablespoons one each tortilla and roll up.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Pour remainder of sauce over top.
Sprinkle with cheese, green onion tops and paprika, if desired.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: date nut log
directions: Mix oleo, dates, sugar, egg and vanilla; cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Roll into a log until firm.
Coat with coconut.
Refrigerate; slice when cold.

title: paolo (helen's) chili
directions: Drain and rinse the beans, easily done using a colander. Brown the meat and onions.
Drain off excess fat.
Using blender or food processor, mix the remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low for about 1 hour, stirring often.

title: orange coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reunion salad
directions: Mix jello with water until dissolved. Add juice from beets and pineapple. Refrigerate until thickened. Dice beets small.

title: dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole
dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: relish
directions: Grind vegetables using coarse food chopper blade.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling point, then simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: easy sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add other ingredients. Mix well and chill until firm.

title: mrs. shepard's mulligan
directions: Layer potatoes, onions, peas, hamburger, potatoes and onions. Cover with tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in two 8 or 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured well.
When cool, split each layer in half horizontally.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipped topping.
Divide this filling between the two cake "bottoms."
Place cake "tops" on.
Frost.

title: quick 'n easy 4-minute butter frosting
directions: Cream thoroughly butter, salt and 1 cup powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Add remaining powdered sugar and milk, alternating blending until smooth and of spreading consistency. Add vanilla.
Fills and frost top and sides of two 9-inch layers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta. Drain and rinse in cold water. Add other ingredients.

title: donna blalock chicken recipe
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cube.
Mix together sour cream and cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup.
Divide Ritz cracker crumbs in half.
Melt butter or margarine and pour in 9-inch square pan. Pour half of crumbs in pan.
Add chicken, sour cream and soup and then rest of cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: savory meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into meatballs about 1 inch in diameter.
Brown in a skillet over medium heat; drain. For sauce, mix the soup and water together and pour over browned meatballs. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
These are super served on a bed of noodles or rice.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Mix with the next 4 ingredients.
Place 4 uncooked noodles into a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of beef mixture over noodles, then place 4 more noodles.
Spread remaining beef mixture over noodles.
Then put 4 more noodles on top.
Mix water and salsa and pour over the top of noodles.
Let sit overnight in fridge.
The next day, bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until noodles are tender.
Then mix sour cream, green onions and black olives.
Spread over lasagna and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for another 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.	VERY DELICIOUS!

title: banana cookies
directions: Cut margarine into the dry ingredients.
Add the oatmeal as for pastry.
Add the rolled oats, mashed bananas, egg and the chocolate pieces last.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven.
Remove from pan immediately; cool on racks.
Will make 3 dozen cookies.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops; arrange in bottom of baking dish. Cut onion in 4 slices and place slice on each chop.
Cut pepper in 4 rings and place on onion slice.
Add cup of rice.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Dilute soup with 1 can of water. Pour over all.
Add more water if desired.
Place in oven and bake for 1 hour in medium oven at 375° to 400°.
Baste occasionally.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Blend well, add bananas and beat well.
Add flour and soda, beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning mix.
Layer all these ingredients in dish in ordered listed.
Serve with large size Fritos.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In a pan melt the butter, remove from heat, stir in cocoa and cool, and set aside. In a mixing bowl beat eggs and sugar, and set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt and gradually add to egg and sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla and add cooled chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9
inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 - 28 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center is clean. Cool before frosting.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter Crisco, regular Crisco, water and sugar. Add flavorings. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour alternately with sour cream and milk. Add baking powder and salt. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: "red" cucumber pickles
directions: Heat until red hots are melted.
(Takes quite a while.) Stir occasionally.
Add pickles and bring to a boil.
Put into jars and seal.
Happy canning!

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until transparent.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven to 225°. Cook rice in boiling salt water, drain well.
Blend with onions, cheese and half and half.
Taste to season with salt.
Turn into shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 hour.
Great served with baked ham.

title: frittata(italian omelet)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks until frothy.
Add zucchini, cheese, salt and pepper.
Fold in whites.
Pour in a nonstick skillet.
Cook until bottom is brown, then place skillet under broiler as close to heat as possible.
Cook until omelet is browned and puffy.
Serve with tomato sauce.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan cook pudding and milk over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar together in a bowl until small crumbs form. Sprinkle crumb mixture into pie shell.
Pour pudding over crumbs. Chill until set.
Spread whipped topping over pie.

title: oven stew
directions: Drain all vegetables except tomatoes. Add in order listed. Bake at 250° for 6 to 7 hours with cover.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix together the sugar, shortening and eggs thoroughly. Stir in buttermilk, mashed bananas and flour, then stir in soda and fold in nuts.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Doubles nicely.

title: "miss" myra's macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
When mixture starts to boil, add cheese, stirring constantly.
When cheese is completely melted, pour over macaroni.
Use a 2-quart baking dish, sprayed with Pam or rubbed with margarine or oil.
Cook in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: hemmels sutter
directions: Mix the first six ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 1/2 hour at 325°.
Cool.
Cut or break up.
Add remaining ingredients. You can make the crust up ahead of time and freeze.

title: large taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese and spread over large round flat plate/tray.
Cook ground chuck; drain.
Mix in taco mix. Spoon over cheese mixture.
Spread lettuce, then tomatoes, then onions.
Spoon sauce over entire top.
Cover with cheese and decorate with sliced black olives.
Serve with taco chips.

title: sister bertha's frosting
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa and cook one minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well, but fast, because it will set.
Drop on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well on a large piece of waxed paper. Coat each tomato slice well.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown and tender.
The secret to this recipe is getting the oil hot enough.
I like to use a heavy iron skillet.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix all together and put into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate and let set until firm.

title: pumpkin cheesecake pie
directions: Roll graham crackers into fine crumbs.
Combine with brown sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Set aside 1/4 cup of the crumb mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture in to a deep 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 9 minutes.
Cool.

title: mock coconut cookies
directions: Soak sauerkraut in clear water for approximately 5 minutes. Drain and rinse under running water for several minutes.
Drain. In small pan, place kraut, 1/2 cup water and 1 or 2 packages sweetener.
Bring to a boil, simmer until kraut is almost dry, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, sweetener and extract.
Drop by spoonful onto a Teflon cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: mother's summer soup
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Chill. Spoon into soup bowls and garnish with chopped parsley before serving.
Serves 3.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In a small saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, egg and 1 cup pineapple juice. Add water to make 1 cup juice if can does not yield it. Stir constantly until thickened; let cool. Whip cream, then fold into sauce.

title: slurch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a plastic dishwashing tub.
This concoction doesn't hold a shape like play dough, but it makes a wonderful play medium for young ooze-enthusiasts.

title: hollis' homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions, garlic, bell pepper and tomato paste; cook until onions are clear.
Add tomato sauce, refilling the cans with water; add to mixture.
Add ground meat, breaking up as you add. Add seasonings and sugar; season to taste.
Cook at least one hour or longer, up to two or three hours on low fire.
Serve over thin spaghetti noodles.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: chocolate surprise cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Set aside.

title: vancouver potage
directions: Mix all soups and water together, stirring frequently.
Serve hot.

title: best peanut brittle ever
directions: Mix sugar, peanuts, Karo syrup, water and salt in deep pan to a hard crack.
Take off heat.
Add the vanilla and soda; mix fast. While still puffed up, pour into large cookie sheet.
Spread out fast; it sets up quickly.
Let cool 1 hour; break into pieces.

title: white castle sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Sprinkle flour over hamburger. Stir.
Dissolve soup in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add to hamburger; let simmer for 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Serve on buns.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Brown ground beef; add tomatoes, black-eyed peas, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix corn bread according to package directions, then pour corn bread mixture over ground beef and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes or until corn bread is done.
Serve piping hot.

title: caribbean reef chicken
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper over washed and dried chicken. Set aside.

In a small bowl, make Caribbean paste by mixing together sugar, 2 tablespoons of the rum, lime juice, lemon pepper, ginger, cloves, cinnamon, garlic powder and hot pepper sauce; set aside. Place the chicken, skin side up, in a large shallow baking pan. Rub Caribbean paste evenly over the chicken. Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes or until the chicken is fork-tender.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup of pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, salt and water in pan.
Let stand 2 hours; drain, but don't rinse, then add sugar, vinegar and dill. Let stand and stir until sugar has dissolved and liquid covers cucumbers and onions.
Pack in containers and freeze.

title: pot roast and veggies
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Place roast in bottom of a large pan and pour in enough water to cover meat well.
Stir in soup.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer with lid on.
Cook 2 to 3 hours total.
(Add water as necessary to keep meat and veggies covered.) About 3/4 hour before meat is done, add potatoes and carrots and continue to simmer.

title: chocolate peanut butter brownies(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven at 350.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken broth.
Drain, but keep broth.
Mix vegetables, chicken, spaghetti, soup, 1/2 of the cheese and broth together.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle with the rest of the cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: corn salad
directions: Thaw corn.
Chop green pepper, onion, cucumber and tomato into small pieces.
Mix with corn and marinate in dressing overnight. Serve as a cold salad.

title: lemon-sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Slowly stir in milk and cook until thickened.
Blend small amount of hot mixture into the slightly beaten egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cover and cool. Fold in sour cream.
Pour in baked crust and top with meringue.

title: cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill.

title: camper's country breakfast
directions: Cook bacon; remove and drain.
Saute potatoes, peppers and onion until potatoes are brown and veggies are soft.
Add beaten eggs.
Cover and cook until done.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together (do not beat).
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes

title: lite trio salad
directions: Arrange greens on 4 salad plates. Arrange meat and fruit slices in a circle over greens. Use 1/4 cup of yogurt on each place as a dressing or serve in a small bowl for dipping. Sprinkle walnuts over the top of salad, if desired. Serve with low-fat muffin.

title: dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 4 minutes. Pour into generously greased and floured pans.
Use two 9-inch or three 8-inch round pans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Frost with at least 2 1/2 cups of your favorite frosting.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Mix all.
Place in buttered pan.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over oatmeal; cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat the butter until creamy.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and the eggs.
Add oatmeal mixture; mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices; mix.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cherry or blueberry crunch
directions: Melt 2 sticks oleo; blend in 2 cups of flour and chopped nuts with a fork.
Press into pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Chill several hours before serving.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix undiluted orange and grapefruit concentrates, water, apricot nectar and pineapple juice together.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Alternate cherries and pineapple chunks on plastic straws to make kabobs.
Place in tall glasses with ice. Pour in punch.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: lemon-poppy seed bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan). Combine milk and poppy seed.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening thoroughly with sugar.
Beat eggs and lemon rind into creamed mixture.
Blend in flour alternately with milk mixture, beating well after each addition.
Turn mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels with 3 tablespoons sugar and 3/4 cup melted margarine.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat it down to make a crust.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overbake. Let cool.

title: chicken fried round steak
directions: Pound round steak thoroughly;
cut into serving pieces. Blend egg and
milk.
Dip
meat in egg mixture then in crumbs. Slowly brown
meat
in
hot oil, turning once; season.
Cover; cook over low heat 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: "recess" peanut butter cups
directions: Over hot, not boiling, water in a double boiler, combine both chocolates, paraffin and 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Stir until smooth. Spoon half of chocolate mixture equally among 24 to 30 liners (about 1 tablespoon each) in miniature tart tins or cupcake liners cut to 1-inch depth.
Let set in a cool place for 5 minutes.

title: hidden treasure cake
directions: Mix above ingredients with mixer. Pour 1/2 batter in bundt pan that is greased and floured OR sprayed with PAM.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Just heat and serve.

title: easy chicken
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Put 1 slice of cheese over each breast.
Mix together soup and wine and pour over the chicken.
Add melted margarine to stuffing mix and put on top of cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Uncover for the last 10 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom OR chicken soup

title: really good ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soups and tomatoes (can use blender or put in pan and heat until mixed well).
Layer in a casserole 1/2 package of Doritos, 1/2 meat, 1/2 cheese (cubed), rest of Doritos, meat, all of soup and rest of cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: warm broccoli 'n cheddar dip
directions: Combine mix, sour cream, broccoli and 3/4 cup of the cheese. Top with remaining 1/4 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or Doritos.

title: tex-mex stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour. In a medium saucepan, brown beef, onion and garlic. Drain fat. Add beans, salsa and pepper. Simmer, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until thickened. Cut an X in top of each potato. Fluff potato with fork and spoon beef mixture over each potato. Garnish with sour cream. Sprinkle with green onion and tomato. Serve with chips.

title: pizza spaghetti pie
directions: Combine hamburger, bread crumbs,
onion,
salt,
pepper and evaporated milk.
Press firmly onto bottom
and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35
to
40 minutes.
Spoon off drippings.

title: gingerbread batter
directions: Mix.
Beat until smooth.
Store in airtight jar for up to 2 months.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes when ready to serve.

title: squash dressing - southern style
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased casserole and bake at 375° for 40 minutes. This recipe freezes well and can be prepared ahead.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes. Rinse under cold water. Into a large bowl filled with cold water, coarsely shred the potatoes and onion.
In colander lined with paper towel, drain potatoes and onion. Wrap potatoes and onion in towel.
Squeeze as much water as possible from them.
In the same bowl, beat eggs.
Add potatoes, onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Toss until well mixed.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in 1/3 cup hot oil, drop potato mixture by scant 1/4 cup into 4 mounds.
Flatten each pancake and cook about 4 minutes on each side.
Drain.
Makes about 16 pancakes.

title: patricia's peanut butter oatmeal fudge
directions: Stir while melting on low, Butter, Sugar and Milk.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute, no stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add Vanilla, Peanut Butter, Oatmeal and Walnuts.
Mix well, place in pan sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Drain and add the tuna.
Add the mushroom soup.
Mix and add enough milk to make it smooth and not dry (probably about 4 cups).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, covered with foil.
When bubbling, take foil off and add crushed potato chips on top.
Bake about 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: seafood cocktail puffs
directions: Combine salad dressing mix with biscuit mix.
Toss with seafood.
In separate bowl, whisk together egg and milk.
Add to seafood mixture, combining well.
In deep fryer, heat 1/2-inch oil to 375°.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of batter into oil, one at a time.
Fry in batches until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes, turning to brown on all sides.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Arrange on serving platter; garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.
Serve with Spicy Party Dip.

title: macho matzo brie
directions: Cut up onion, pepper, garlic and tomato.
Heat up skillet with olive oil.
Brown cut up ingredients in skillet.
While browning, break eggs in bowl.
Wet matzo under faucet and break up into bowl with eggs.
Add splash of water to egg and matzo mixture; stir until mixed together well.
Add spices and hot sauce; mix.
Pour mixture over onion, peppers and garlic.
Let cook until bubbles appear and bottom has browned.
Flip over and brown other side. Serves 1 or 2.
Enjoy!!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Crumble shrimp. Stir in mayonnaise, onion and salsa. Chill for 1 to 2 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: crock-pot goulash(serves 6)
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Put in crock-pot, along with tomatoes (cut up), tomato sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms and green pepper.
Set crock-pot on high for 2 1/2 hours.
Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Add to crock-pot and cook for 1/2 hour.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: veal loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk;
stir
in bread crumbs, shredded carrot, chopped onion, snipped
parsley, salt and pepper.
Add the ground veal; mix well.
Pat veal
mixture
into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in
a
oven
about
1/2 hours. Drain off excess fat; let
loaf
stand
for
15 minutes before turning out of pan.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato cookies
directions: Combine cooled melted margarine with coconut flavoring and egg.
Combine Bisquick, potato flakes and sugar.
Combine these 2 mixtures.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle a little stuffing on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: stolen pumpkin pie
directions: Blend together and pour into deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, shred lettuce in bite size pieces in bottom of pan.
Layer onion, green pepper, celery, peas (barely cook and cool first) and add other half of lettuce on top.
Spread mayonnaise and sprinkle sugar, Parmesan cheese, and bacon bits before serving.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
For extra flavor, chives, parsley, onion, rosemary or marjoram can be added.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Place the butter, Splenda Granular, brown sugar, and vanilla in a medium mixing bowl. Mix, using the paddle attachment of an electric mixer until the mixture is light and creamy. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Add peanut butter and stir until well mixed. Add chocolate and mix briefly.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let strawberries thaw so they do not stick together in chunks.
Mash bananas with fork. Mix all fruits together.
Pour Jell-O over mixture.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a flat bottom dish.
After it has congealed, pour 1 carton sour cream over mixture and then pour the rest of the mixture over that.
Return to refrigerator to finish congealing. Makes 10 servings.

title: shrimp or crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onions,
celery
and bell pepper until clear; add Ro-Tel tomatoes and garlic powder and cook for 5 minutes.	Add mushroom soup and
water; this is to be cooked a while longer. Soak bread in	water,	squeeze
water out and break into small pieces;

add to cooked mixture.	Then add crawfish or shrimp, rice and parsley. Cook 10 minutes; finally, pour into 2 quart buttered casserole and sprinkle top with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.	Bake uncovered at 450° until brown.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: You will need a 20-gallon pot with a lift out basket (smaller, if you have a small group).

title: guy's skillet pheasant
directions: Cut pheasant into chunks; roll in seasoned flour.
Brown in butter.
Add onion soup mix (following soup directions on package).
Add diced onion; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat. Spoon off fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes. Cook noodles and drain.
Rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Place noodles in baking dish. Spread with 1/2 cottage cheese filling. Add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
May be prepared early and refrigerated.
Allow 15 minutes extra or so for baking.
May freeze, also.

title: little shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil in large skillet over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Break up and add meat.
Cook and stir until meat loses pink color, about 5 minutes.
Drain fat.
Mix in salt and pepper and set aside.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Then add the rest so the oil and rest won't separate so much.

title: crackerjackets
directions: Break crackers along perforations into squares or rectangles. Wrap each bacon slice securely around each cracker, covering cracker entirely and tucking bacon ends underneath.
Place wrapped crackers on rack of broiler pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Drain on paper towels. Refrigerate (or freeze, if desired). Before serving, place on rack in broiler pan and reheat in a 350° oven. Drain again and serve hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk.
Fold in confectioners sugar.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix bread, sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Add milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half and sugar until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pout 1 cup half and half into mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat until well blended.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices and mix well.
Spread over cream layer. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine broccoli, raisins and onoins. In small bowl, combine sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli.
Toss to coat.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon and sunflower seeds.
Toss. Yields 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Drop from teaspoon and press down. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: wintery day bean soup
directions: Place beans in pot and soak overnight with 2 tablespoons salt. In the morning, drain off the water the beans soaked in.
Add 2 quarts water and all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cold fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix margarine, nuts and flour.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Microwave cauliflower until thawed enough to break apart. Place in oblong casserole dish (one layer deep).
Pour melted margarine over this. Cover with grated Swiss cheese,
Parmesan cheese and top with bread crumbs.
(If you really like Swiss cheese, you can add more.)

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add crushed pineapple, eggs and nuts. Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine dry jello and cottage cheese.
Add drained crushed pineapple and cool whip.
Chill.
Serves 6-8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter together.
Add sugar and Cool Whip and mix.
Divide into the pie crusts and refrigerate. Use the rest of the Cool Whip for the pie tops.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with the milk to the sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
When cake is cool, punch holes in cake.
Top with strawberries and Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: skillet squash
directions: Saute onion in shortening until soft; add squash and stir until almost done.
Add chiles; cook over very low fire.
Sprinkle over cheese and stir until cheese is melted but not stringy. Serves 3 or 4.

title: mama's cole slaw
directions: Put the vinegar and sugar on stove and heat.
Add beaten egg in a separate dish with a little bit of warm mixture.
Stir.
Add to remaining vinegar mixture.
Cook until thickened or cloudy. Remove from heat.
Cool and add to cabbage.
Add salt and pepper. Add mayonnaise to taste.
Stir and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in saltwater. Leave 1 1/2 quarts broth to cook spaghetti. Saute onion, pepper and celery in 1 stick butter. Add chicken pieces, peas, tomatoes, cheese and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well. Pour in casserole dish with spaghetti. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir in sherbet.
Add fruit, nuts and cottage cheese.
Chill to set.
Serves 6 to 8 with luncheon or dinner.
This is very sweet but the cottage cheese cuts the sweetness.

title: steak a la creole
directions: Salt and pepper the meat.
In an iron skillet, brown the meat in shortening.
Remove and set aside.
Make a roux by browning flour along with onion and green pepper in the fat remaining in the skillet.
Add water, tomatoes and seasonings.
Allow to simmer for about 30 minutes.
Return meat to gravy and cook until tender. Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground meat and drain off grease.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until rice is done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute vegetables.
Combine all ingredients.
Cover with bread crumbs in buttered casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately.
Coat blackberries with a small amount of flour; add to other ingredients and mix well.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease muffin cups or use liners.
Mix sugar, sweet potatoes, butter and eggs together.
In another bowl, mix the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix dry ingredients with wet ingredients alternately with the milk, stirring just to blend.
Do not overmix!
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into muffin cups and sprinkle each with sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Bake 20- 25 minutes and serve warm. Makes
2-2 1/2 dozen.
Freeze any left over and heat up in microwave when needed.

title: delicious potato salad
directions: Chop and simmer vegetables in the water for 15 minutes.
Cook margarine and flour over medium heat; add the vegetables along with milk, cheese and ham, then picante sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Cook at 325° slowly until it gets done.

title: magetti
directions: Brown beef.
Cook together onions, celery, pepper stirring often.
Cook noodles according to pkg.
Combine onion, celery, pepper and soups with beef and noodles and cook slowly for a few minutes.
Top with strips of cheese; cook only until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle 1 tsp garlic salt over top.

title: holiday bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans onto a pie plate.
Spoon picante sauce over it.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Top with onions and serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese.
Combine all ingredients except paprika.
Roll into a ball.
Roll in paprika to coat.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add the eggs and fruit cocktail; beat well.
Bake in greased pan at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: bananas barbara
directions: In small skillet, place butter and melt over medium heat.
Add brown sugar slowly while stirring.
Add lemon juice and stir.
Add rum.
Stir and then add cut up bananas (4-inch split pieces). Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve over vanilla ice cream.
Serves 5 to 6.
Quick, easy way to use leftover or aging bananas.

title: dough dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Split hot dogs almost through and fill with cheese.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly a few times.
Roll into a rectangle on a floured surface.
Cut into 8 rectangles.
Spread each with a little mustard.
Wrap each hot dog in dough, tucking in the ends and sealing with a little cold water.
Place seam side down on a greased baking sheet and bake about 12 minutes, until nicely browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Then put into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve with Melba rounds or Ritz crackers.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain and rinse.
Put sausage in bottom of crock-pot.
Break cheese up into small pieces.
Put over sausage. Pour milk on top of both.
Add 5 ounces water.
Heat on low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally to blend.
Serve over white tortilla chips.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put ham hock and beans in large pot.
Cover with water.
Season with salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cook over low fire 4 to 5 hours, or until meat falls off bone and beans are done.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham and cheese
directions: Melt soup and cheese in pan.
Pour over potatoes in casserole and stir in ham.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces.
Place cabbage, sugar, salt, rice and oleo in 2 cups water.
Cook until rice is done.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes on medium speed until smooth.
Add nuts and chocolate chips; stir to blend.
Bake in oiled and floured Bundt pan 50 to 60 minutes at 350° or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: company chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoning salt. Grease 3-quart casserole well and spread rice over bottom.
Layer with mushrooms, then chicken.
Mix undiluted soups with savory and dry soup mix.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Pour broth around sides to moisten rice.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: The 4 teaspoons of soda makes candy airy/crunchy.

title: lemon gem miniature cakes
directions: Prepare cake batter using package directions.
Spoon by teaspoonfuls into greased and floured miniature muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Combine confectioners sugar, lemon juice and rind in small bowl; stir until sugar dissolves.
Place wire racks over waxed paper.
Dip hot miniature cakes in glaze.
Place on wire racks to cool completely.
Yield:
96 servings.

title: elva's chicken bake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in large pan.
Mix cracker crumbs with margarine and put over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Grease baking dish. Place ingredients in order and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, carrots, garlic in enough water to cover potatoes.
In medium cooker cook until tender about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain over have the water off but not all the water.
Add 1/2 of the chicken broth.
Bring to boil; mix remaining chicken broth and corn starch and pour into potatoes.
Add milk, butter, salt, and pepper stir together and let simmer for 5 minutes.

title: thick-n-creamy cheese dip
directions: In a large microwave safe bowl, add rotel and soup and heat on high for 5 minutes.
Then add cheese and heat on high for 10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.
Also great when you add your favorite chili to it. Just mix 1-1/2 cups of your favorite chili to cheese dip and heat up.
Make approx. 8 servings.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time. Blend in the almond extract.
Sift flour with the baking powder and salt and stir into the first mixture.
Add the lemon rind, juice and nuts.
Do not beat, but stir only enough to moisten. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine milk and cream in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Cook until rice is tender, "creamy" liquid is absorbed, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Butter 2-quart baking dish. Beat egg yolks until frothy; beat in sugar, salt and vanilla. Stir in hot rice, small portion at a time.
Beat the egg whites to soft peaks.
Fold in rice mixture.
Put in baking dish; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place baking dish in shallow pan; add 2-inches hot water to pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fatman's pie
directions: Mix pudding by instant pudding on box for pie filling.
Mix together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Place sugar and cream cheese mixture on crust, then pudding and top with Cool Whip. Chill for 1 hour.

title: italian chicken
directions: Combine vermouth, bouillon, water, garlic powder, oregano, parsley and salt and pepper and pour one-half of the mixture into a baking dish.
Place raw chicken in dish and add cut up potatoes, to suit, around chicken.
Add remaining mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in oven at 375° to 400°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Do not turn chicken.

title: halloween jello squares
directions: Mix the 4 boxes of Knox gelatine into boiling water; stir until dissolved, then add 3 packages of Jell-O.
Stir and put into clear 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put into refrigerator until cold, then cut into squares and serve.

title: sarah's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, then chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in bananas and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus in a blanket
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place 4 spears of asparagus on each ham slice and roll up.
Put into baking dish.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cherries.
Put into square plastic container and put into freezer.
Decorate with cherries. Take out of freezer about half an hour before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well and mix with other ingredients except pecans. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell to which nuts have been added. Bake in 350° oven until the custard has set, about 40 minutes or when it begins to crack.

title: fried ripe plantain(fried sweet bananas)
directions: Peel plantain.
Slice long way in about 3 to 4-inch each slice.
Heat oil in frying pan on medium.
Place plantains in hot oil.
Turn over when other side browns.
When both sides are done, take out and drain on paper towel.
Serve as an appetizer or side vegetable.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash, drain and hull strawberries.
Spread softened cream cheese over bottom of cooled, baked pie shell.
Cover with 1/2 of the berries (the best ones).
Mash remaining berries and, if necessary, add a little water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring this mixture to a boil and gradually stir in a mixture of sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Boil one minute (mixture goes from cloudy to clear). Cool.
Pour over berries in pie shell.
Chill about 2 to 4 hours. Just before serving, decorate with whipped cream.

title: rum brownies dessert
directions: Crumble cookies or brownies in a Tupperware container.	Pour over at least 1/2 c. rum and refrigerate.
Next day, taste for rum flavor and add more if necessary.
Stir in a container of Cool Whip.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sausage and drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in small amount of sausage grease; drain.
Combine cheese and flour.
Stir in sausage, pepper and onion.
Spread on top of croutons in 9 x 12-inch lightly greased dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over sausage mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until filling is set.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Chop and mix first 6 ingredients and place in casserole.
Pour butter and milk over top.
Put cornflakes on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: monte's cheese soup
directions: Saute onions, carrots and celery in butter in a large pan for 5 minutes or until tender.
Add flour and cornstarch, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and chicken broth. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in soda and cheese. Reduce to low heat and cook until cheese melts.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli, margarine and onion.
Then mix this mixture with rest of the ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Put flour, mustard, salt and pepper in plastic bag and shake; add meat and toss to coat well.
Spray a medium sized skillet with Pam or nonstick cooking spray and quickly brown meat over medium-high heat.
Add water, vinegar, onion slices, brown sugar, bay leaf and cloves to meat.
When boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until meat is tender.
While meat is cooking, cook noodles according to package directions in a large saucepan.
(Use 4 cups hot water instead of following directions). Drain.
Crumble gingersnaps and add to meat mixture.
Cook and stir about 5 minutes until it is thickened.
Remove and discard the bay leaf.
Serve over the hot noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach crunch
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the yogurt and 1 1/2 teaspoons of apple pie spice.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Spray a small skillet with no stick spray.
Add margarine and heat over medium heat until melted.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rice and cook five minutes, stirring constantly.
Add soup, 1 can of water and mushrooms. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 370°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Ritz crackers.
Put in greased casserole; top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: marzipan
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.
Shape into small fruits and vegetables by hand or use small candy molds. If desired, use food coloring to paint details on fruit.
Add whole cloves, citron or angelica for stems and blossom ends. Chill until dry.
Then store at room temperature, in covered container.
Makes about 36 confections.

title: amma's cranberry salad
directions: Cook berries in water until berries "pop".
Force mixture through food mill.
Add sugar to strained berries.
Mix well and boil 5 minutes.
Put gelatine in 2 tablespoons cold water.
Mix well and add to cranberry mixture.
Boil again for 1 to 2 minutes. Cool until partially set.
Add celery, nuts and olives.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8. Much, much tastier than recipe sounds!

title: lemon lust
directions: Combine softened butter, flour and nuts into a pie crust. Spread in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (pat down).
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes and cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream thoroughly shortening and sugar. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and mix.
Chill dough 1 hour.

title: salmon and eggs
directions: Cook salmon in small amount of oil or shortening, until tender. Beat eggs, and seasoning.
Add to salmon.
Cook until eggs are done.
Serve biscuits.

title: red salmon mold
directions: Drain salmon and save liquid.
Flake salmon and mix with celery and onion.
Mix the two envelopes of gelatine with 1/2 cup of cold water.
Combine the liquid saved from salmon with catsup and vinegar.
Boil and stir in the softened gelatine mix.
Blend into salmon mix.
Stir in mayo.
Coat inside of mold with mayo.
Pour in mixture.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with lettuce and parsley.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Pour sugar over bananas and let set for 15 minutes. Blend in shortening. Add sifted flour and baking powder. Dissolve salt and soda in water, then add to mixture. Add eggs and nuts. Stir well. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes in greased pans: 2 medium loaves for 50 minutes or 42 mini muffin for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion. Add broccoli, soup and cheese. Add rice.
Bring to boil; put in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen salad slices
directions: Blend cheese and salad dressing; add fruits, olives, nuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in a 1-quart loaf pan or refrigerator tray.
Freeze firm.
Cut in slices and serve; serves 6 to 8.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat until smooth.
Melt shortening in skillet and do not grease any more.
Turn pancakes when bubbles appear on the surface.

title: swedish sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well. Form in walnut size balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Flatten with glass.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugars and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat until smooth.
In separate bowl mix flour and baking soda.
Add to the butter mixture, then stir in the candy.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 8 (4-inch) cookies.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Line pans with waxed paper.
Makes 2 large loaves or 4 small loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on rack 5 minutes.
Peel paper off cakes and allow to cool on rack.
Brush loaves with brandy if desired.
Wrap in Saran Wrap, then aluminum foil.
Keep well refrigerated.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except Cheddar cheese and pimentos.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and pimentos over the top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry souffle
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water.
Add syrup drained from strawberry halves.
Gradually blend mayonnaise and orange juice with cream cheese.
Stir in gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: southern pecan pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together and pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Set oven on 375° for 10 minutes.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Combine juices to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add water, if needed.
Bring juice to a boil.
Pour over jello and dissolve.
Let it cool.
Add Coke.
Place in refrigerator until mixture begins to thicken.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Pour in mold and let set in refrigerator until firm.
(Three ounces cream cheese may be added, if desired.
Add with hot juices.)

title: old fashion walnut cake
directions: Cream
sugar, butter, salt and egg yolks together.
Add flour and
baking
powder and milk.
Add vanilla and walnuts. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Grease 2 (9-inch) pans with Crisco and line with wax
paper,
dust
with
flour.
Bake
to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Soak in well beaten eggs for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in butter until done. Place chicken and juices in casserole.
Place mushrooms on chicken.
Pour broth over this and top with the sliced cheese. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: adelle payne's pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and flour alternately, mixing well between each addition.
Add flavorings. Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 50 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Let rest in pan until cake begins to pull away from pan, about 10 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients (except cheese and potato chips), as for a salad.
Spread in Pyrex cake baking dish.
Shred Cheddar cheese and spread over crab mixture.
Crush package of potato chips as finely as possible and use to top dish.
Brown in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with green salad and hot rolls.

title: joan's cranberry gelatin
directions: Place gelatin and boiling water in bowl and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan or your favorite dish with which you like to serve cranberry sauce.

title: mocha fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine hot water and 2 teaspoons granules in a bowl; stir well. Add 2 cups brownie mix, 1 teaspoon vanilla and egg whites; stir until well-blended. Pour mixture into a 9-inch pie plate coated with cooking spray. Bake at 325° for 22 minutes (brownie will be fudgy when tested with a wooden pick). Let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste. Coat with flour and place in about 1/4 inch cooking oil. Fry until light browned over medium heat, about 30 to 40 minutes. (Preheat oven to 400°.) Place chicken on paper towels to drain.
Place chicken in oven pan and cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until done.

title: custard fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cream, egg and salt.
Cook until thick. Cool.
Drain pineapple and cut grapes in half; removing seeds. Combine pineapple, grapes, nuts and marshmallows.
Pour cool custard over this and fold in whipped cream.
Chill in refrigerator for about 12 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, butter, and vanilla in bowl. Mix sugar and flour in another bowl. Mix dry ingredients in with wet ingredients and stir together. Place pecans in bottom of pie crust. Pour mixed ingredients over pecans. Take your fingers and dip then in water to wet them,
rub wet fingers over crust that is exposed. This will caramelize the exposed crust for better baking.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add corn, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: wild rice shrimp bayou
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, make sauce by melting butter over low heat.
Mix in flour, salt and pepper.
When bubbly, remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add cream cheese; stir with wire whip until smooth. Arrange asparagus spears on bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix shrimp and mushrooms with rice and spoon over asparagus.
Top with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach chutney
directions: Put the onion, garlic and raisins through food chopper.
Put all ingredients in a large pot and boil 1 hour or until chutney is a rich brown color and rather thick.
Pour while hot into 3 hot pint jars and seal at once.

title: chinese new year rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients; cook and stir until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop ham and onion finely.
Place in a large bowl.
Add cheese, egg, pepper and mustard.
Stir to combine. Spray a mini muffin pan with vegetable oil spray.
Unroll crescent rolls and press dough into one large rectangle.
Cut rectangle into 24 pieces.
Place the dough pieces in the mini muffin cups.
Place a small amount of ham mixture in center of each dough cup.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 24 appetizers.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: In medium saucepan, combine corn syrup and cream.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate; stir until completely melted.
Serve warm as a dip for fruit.

title: nacho dip
directions: In a pie dish, spread layer of sour cream.
Add salsa; top with Cheddar cheese.
Place peppers on top.
Good with the Tostitos chips.

title: poor man's pizza
directions: Place tortillas flat on a cookie sheet.
Lightly spoon pizza sauce onto tortillas.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese or Cheddar cheese and any other items you wish.
Place in a 425° oven until tortillas turn a light golden brown.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy in double boiler.
Pour condensed milk in and stir. Add enough milk until thin enough to pour into ice cream freezer. Add remaining milk to full line on freezer.
Process the same as homemade ice cream.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Squeeze excess juice from vegetables.
Mix and refrigerate overnight or 1 day before making sandwiches.
Spread each piece of bread with mayonnaise.
Makes 50 to 60 party sandwiches.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix everything together. Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt the baking chocolate in a double boiler over simmering water.
Add the condensed milk and stir over the boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add the water and blend well.
Cool, then add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly whipped cream.
Pour into a chilled pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) and place in freezer and freeze.
Serve individually with fancy wafers if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole (eggplant)
directions: Peel eggplant.
Slice and cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash eggplant. Add all ingredients, except cheese and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Use buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer eggplant mixture, then cheese and crumbs and then another layer on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: creole court bouillon with rice
directions: Heat oil.
Stir in flour and instant chicken bouillon.
Add onion, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook and stir until vegetables are nearly tender.
Stir in tomatoes, parsley, water, salt, pepper, red pepper and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add fish; cook 15 minutes.
Ladle into serving bowls and top with 1/2 cup of rice.
Serves 10.

title: sweet n' sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple (keep juice).
In skillet, brown bite-sie pieces of chicken in cooking spray.
Meanwhile, mix water with artificial sweetener.
Add pineapple juice, water/sugar mixture, vinegar, garlic and soy sauce to chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat 40 minutes.
Add green peppers and pineapple chunks.
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Combine cornstarch with cold water and add to simmering mixture.
Stir slowly until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Split into 4 layers.
Make filling by cooking the 1 cup sugar and cream for 5 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows, vanilla and coconut; beat well and spread between each layer.

title: christmas cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar and wine. Fold in egg whites (that have been beaten stiffly). Add flour and baking powder. Last, add fruits and nuts. Bake 2 hours at 275° in a large tube pan or 2 loaf pans that have been greased and lightly floured.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Pour onto a paper towel; let set and drain.
Cut cheese in small pieces.
Put in crock-pot; add Ro-Tel tomatoes and sausage.
Stir.
Heat until all cheese is melted. Eat with your favorite chip.

title: old virginian carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, blend sugar with oil; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, instant tea powder, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda, cloves and salt; mix thoroughly.
Fold in 2 cups of carrots and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 70 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely before glazing.

title: mississippi stew
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain grease.
Combine remaining ingredients with sausage and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Spread mayonnaise on bread slices.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and add a cucumber slice, then cover with another slice of bread.

title: apple crisp
directions: Sprinkle water and 1/4 cup sugar over fruit.
Mix Bisquick, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Beat egg thoroughly.
Pour over Bisquick mixture in a thin stream, stirring constantly with fork until crumply.
Sprinkle crumbs over fruit and pour 1/4 cup melted butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate yum-yums
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Stir in pecans.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Bake at 375° to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Use caution as cookies burn easily.
May be sprinkled with colored sugar before baking.

title: joggin' in a jug
directions: Mix all in a jug and chill.

title: light and fluffy cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter; press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dissolve jello in water and set aside.
Whip the cream cheese and add sugar.
Mix with fork, then add jello.
Whip milk until it form peaks, then fold in cheese mixture.
Pour into crust. Sprinkle top with crushed graham crackers and refrigerate.
Can be made day before.
Can use other toppings such as thickened strawberries.

title: conch fritters(makes about 50 small fritters.)
directions: Combine all of the ingredients with enough milk for the mixture to hold its shape.
Form into fritters and fry at 350° until golden.
Note that round fritters (small) should have a thicker batter than flat fritters.
Check amount of milk.
Serve with hot sauce of your choice.
Cooking time is approximately 20 minutes for full recipe.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa and milk to soft ball stage.
Make soft ball in cold water to test.
Take off heat; add butter and vanilla. Beat until thick.
Put on greased plate.

title: hamburger pan quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat; drain fat and set aside.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion, pepper and other seasonings.
Pour in pastry shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix well.
Add soda, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Fold in bananas, walnuts and vanilla. Place in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted does not stick.

title: grandma's cobbler
directions: Mix batter, adding butter.
Pour into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Spoon fruit over top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° until top is nicely browned.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like a pie dough.
Fill pan half full of sliced apples; add a little white sugar and 1/2 cup water. Cover with crumb mixture and bake at 400°.

title: eggplant special
directions: Cut eggplant lengthwise; scoop out inside, leaving a 3/4-inch shell.
Place shells on slightly oiled shallow pan.
Chop eggplant pulp.
Cook in butter until clear.
Add onion and garlic; cool. Add bread crumbs, ground beef and egg; season with salt and pepper.
Mound eggplant shells with mixture; brush lightly with oil.
Sprinkle with additional bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with chili sauce or hot catsup.
Serves 4.

title: ricotta bread(bread book - johnson)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and sugar.
Let sit until bubbly. Add juice, honey, eggs, oil, salt, anise, orange peel and cheese. Beat well.
Add 2 cups whole wheat flour and beat vigorously. Gradually add 3 to 4 cups more white flour until the dough starts to pull away from the sides of the bowl.
Turn the dough out onto a floured board and knead until smooth elastic.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla; beat. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine with other mixture. Shape into balls and dip in white sugar (granulated).
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Press in candy kisses and return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: orange-nut bread
directions: Sift first five ingredients together.
Add walnuts.
Add oil, egg and orange juice. Mix slightly.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cover for first 20 minutes to prevent cracking.
Cool on rack.
May be frozen.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, beans, seasoning mix, onion and grated cheese.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll each tortilla tightly, jelly roll fashion, and place seam side down on a baking sheet.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Slice each in 1-inch slices and serve.

title: okra succotash
directions: Rinse okra under running water - drain. Combine ingredients in a large skillet. Cover & simmer for about 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Season to taste.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Heat the butter in a frying pan. Add the onions; saute until the onions are translucent, but not brown.
Combine the salt, pepper, Tabasco, mustard, eggs and sour cream in a medium size bowl; mix well.
Stir in the onions.

Pour the mixture into the pastry shell; top with the grated cheese. Bake for 20 minutes, then reduce the oven temperature to 325° and bake until the filling is set and the top is golden brown, about 20 minutes more.
Let cool for at least 10 minutes before cutting into serving pieces.
Yields 12 first course servings.

title: 24 hour layered salad
directions: Layer 2/3 of the lettuce, all the peas, cheese, onion, celery and then remaining lettuce in a small glass bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Wonderful on wheat rolls.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and slice.
Put in casserole. Boil sugar, margarine and vanilla until thick.
Pour over potatoes; simmer in oven at 350°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Brown chicken breast halves in butter.
Save butter in pan.
Grease 9 x 13 casserole.
Place rice in casserole, top with chicken breast.
To the butter in skillet, add cream of chicken soup, white wine, chopped celery, mushrooms and 2 tablespoons chopped pimento.	Heat to boiling and pour over chicken.
Bake 25 minutes, covered, at 350°, then bake for 15 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: fluffy batter bread
directions: Beat eggs with the sweet and buttermilk.
Melt butter in pan in which bread is to be baked.
Have oven hot before adding dry ingredients to liquids.
Have greased pan hot before adding batter bread.
Put at once into hot (475°) oven and bake until firm in center.

title: burgundy brisket
directions: Combine tomato sauce, wine and soup mix.
Pour over brisket. Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Boil chicken, bone and cut up.
Place broccoli and chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and juice.
Spread over chicken and broccoli.

title: our favorite pickles
directions: Drain pickles; add to cut-up pickles all of the remaining ingredients and let stand outside of refrigerator for 24 hour before refrigerating.

title: play dough with kool-aid
directions: Mix ingredients.
No cooking necessary.
Store in airtight container.
Double recipe for class quantity.
Blue available as well as red, orange, yellow, etc.
Smells, looks and feels great!

title: caramel-scotch sauce
directions: *Be sure to warm whipping cream before adding caramelized sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: In a casserole dish mix potato soup, cheese and onion.
Mix potatoes in with about 1 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Can make ahead and bake later.

title: microwave squash
directions: Wash
squash
and
cut off ends.
Slice squash down the center (lengthwise), leaving seed in.
Place sliced squash in long microwave
dish
and
sprinkle
with
seasoning salt and pepper. Put 1 to 2 pats of margarine on each slice of squash. Seal	with Saran Wrap and cook 15 to 20 minutes, until squash is tender.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all dry ingredients and pour into wet ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate mixture 2 hours.
Make into balls.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: mrs. b's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Slowly add sugar, 1 cup milk and salt.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened (5 to 10 minutes). Slowly add condensed milk and stir well.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into glass jars for Christmas gift giving.
Keeps in the fridge for 1 month.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix horseradish with vinegar.
Add seasonings; stir in cream, whipped stiff.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill or freeze until almost time to serve.

title: fay's yeast biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in water.
Then mix with other ingredients.
Roll out dough; put 3 small balls in each muffin tin.
Let rise.
Bake at 400°.
Top with margarine.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar little at a time and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift three times.
Add the flour mixture little at a time and mix well.
Add flavoring and chill.
Roll dough very thin and cut into desired shapes.
Bake in 400° oven for 6 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple thoroughly in large pot.
Dissolve jello in it. Set aside to cool.
Chop celery and pecans and add to jello mixture.
Add other ingredients as listed, blending well with slotted spoon.
Pour into serving bowl and chill.
May be made a day ahead of time.
Serve on lettuce or alone.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in boiling water.
Beat in cream cheese and refrigerate until almost congealed.
Remove from refrigerator and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple, whipped cream and pecans.
Pour into long shallow dish and refrigerate.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Bring water to boil in saucepan for cooking the macaroni.
Add salt, onion and green pepper to the boiling water before adding the macaroni.
Cook the macaroni according to the package directions until just tender.
Drain.
Turn the heat down low under the saucepan.
Put soup in the saucepan.
Then add the tuna, macaroni and black pepper.
Stir until heated through.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: choco-chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add Pet evaporated milk and butter or margarine. Blend in slightly beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix well and put in an unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: bell dutch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on prepared cookie sheet.
Cook slowly at 300°.

title: strawberry short cake
directions: Measure and sift dry ingredients.
Blend in the egg and milk. Bake in a hot oven at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Split cake and spread with butter.
Sweeten strawberries to taste and put between and on top of shortcake.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: milk shake
directions: Put in blender, on blend, whip, chop, etc., whichever desired.

title: southern style chilli
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until done. Drain and add tomato juice and diced tomatoes into a large pan. Add seasoning and water. Stir and simmer of 2 hours.

title: crispies
directions: Mix first five ingredients and vanilla.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add oatmeal.
Stir well and drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together and add a pinch of garlic salt.
Put all in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with hard crackers.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans and chocolate over bottom of pie shell.
In bowl, mix syrup, sugar and eggs.
Stir in butter.
Pour over mixture in pie shell.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine in bowl with dry cake mix.
Mix until crumbly.
Pour pie filling in bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle crumbly cake mix over fruit.
(You may add some nuts or coconut to cake mix.)
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly brown around edges.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with cooking spray.
Place corn flakes in a Baggie and crush, then set aside.
Beat eggs in a medium sized bowl; add crushed cereal, vegetables, butter, onion and cheese.
Stir to combine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Optional:
add garlic powder.)
Spread mixture in prepared baking dish.
Bake uncovered for 20 to 30 minutes until mixture is hot and bubbly.	Yields 6 servings.

title: deluxe chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: In a mixing bowl cream 3/4 cup butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.

title: chili sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Roll on floured cutting board.
Cut with open end of a tuna can.
Bake at 375° for 14 minutes.

title: zucchini crunch casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until just tender.
Slice. In medium casserole, put layer of zucchini covered with layer of grated cheese and layer of potato chip crumbs.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat until vegetables are used.
Beat egg yolks with milk.
Pour over.
Bake in preheated oven until eggs and milk are set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pink and creamy punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add lemonade and 4 cups cold water.
Add cranberry juice and Hawaiian Punch.
Chill.

title: irish soda bread ii
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cream of tartar, salt, sugar, caraway seed, raisins and pieces of butter.
In a separate bowl combine eggs, buttermilk and sour cream.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid gradually; mix well.
Turn dough onto a floured surface.
Knead lightly for 10 minutes.
Shape into a round loaf, slightly mounded in center and place in cake pan.
Make a cross on the top and sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Place in oven.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes longer.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mommy's rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put strips of crust on top (to make lattice).
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until crust browns.
The Best!

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice.
While still hot, add marshmallows and pineapple. When cool, add whipping cream and sugar.
Decorate as desired.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix cold water with corn meal and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then stir in milk, eggs and lastly, melted shortening.
Mix well and pour into a heated, well-greased casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 50 minutes or until the top is firm and well browned.
If any is left over, it is good warmed over with a lump of butter on top.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Whip the first 4 ingredients; pour over cooled crust.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Let stand at least 3 hours before serving, providing you have enough willpower.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Poach chicken breasts, skin, cut into pieces.
Place soups, sour cream, cream cheese and salt in saucepan.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a layer of thawed and drained broccoli; cover with 1/3 of the cream sauce, some chicken pieces and noodles.
Repeat for 3 layers.
Top with grated Parmesan or Pecurino cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: moo's corn casserole
directions: Saute onion
and pepper in butter, then mix corn, Jiffy mix and eggs.
Mix
well.
Add in onion and pepper.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch
greased
pan.
Top
with
sour cream and cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy, but not stiff.
Stir in the sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add pecans and stir until completely covered.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 200° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: potatoes baked in milk
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and peel the potatoes and cut into thin slices.
Butter a baking dish and arrange the potato slices in layers.
Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper and cake flour and dot with butter.
Place onion rings between sliced potatoes. Pour milk over the potatoes to cover halfway.
Cover with a lid and bake for 1 hour.
Remove the lid and bake for another 15 minutes until brown.
Sprinkle with grated cheese before baking.

title: fried squash
directions: Slice squash.
Add chopped onion with sliced potatoes in hot vegetable oil.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat, stirring off and on, until done.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
