directions: Mix together coconut and nuts.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hamburger chowder
directions: In a soup kettle, brown ground beef with
onion; drain drippings from pan.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: barbie cups
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add barbecue sauce; mix.
Press biscuit dough in muffin cups.
Add heaping spoonful of meat.
Top with cross made of cheese.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: fresh applesauce cake
directions: According to size of apples, process enough to produce 2 1/2 cups of applesauce.
In hot applesauce add soda and then butter. Add sugar and remaining ingredients, stir well.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
This is a large cake.

title: broccoli bake casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Drain, if using onions, add to broccoli.
Melt cheese and 1/2 of margarine and add to broccoli.
Pour in greased medium casserole.
Melt remaining margarine and add to crumbled crackers.
Spread on the broccoli. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or bubbly at 350°.
If using microwave, bake until hot and bubbly.
Freezes well.

title: date-oatmeal squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring often until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: fresh carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in an ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Mix well.
Add carrots until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Scrape pan clean.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until done.
Cool in pan on rack.
Cut into squares.

title: 10 can chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the onion rings, together.
Put into a 3-quart casserole; top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: low sodium fat biscuit mix
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder and sugar thoroughly. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Store covered in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks or freeze for up to 6 months.

title: rum bay restaurant's key lime pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large, heat resistant glass bowl.
Mix well.
Place bowl over a pot of boiling water.
Whisk vigorously until mixture is light yellow and a soft pudding texture.
Remove from boiling water.
Add butter and margarine. Stir until blended.
Add condensed milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill overnight.
Top with whipped cream.

title: orange pound cake(low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pam spray and flour an 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
Sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Add oil, juice and orange rind.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Bake until cake springs back when lightly touched, about 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions, celery, rice, soups and a little water and soy sauce.
Top with noodles.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab stuffing
directions: Saute onion, celery, and pepper in butter until soft.
Add shrimp and mushrooms. Cover to produce liquid, uncover and cook until shrimp are barely pink.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir and cook 5-6 minutes.
You may then stuff fish baking at 10 minutes per pound; or large shrimp butterflied; or Portobello mushrooms.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Saute onion and peppers in butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over cooked rice. Serves 8.

title: apple finger cubes
directions: Pour gelatin into a bowl.
Add 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add apple juice concentrate.
Pour mixture into lightly greased cake pan and chill.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked rice and put into casserole. Cook 45 minutes at 325°.

title: quick toast cups
directions: Melt butter and brush inside of miniature muffin cups. Cut circles of bread with biscuit cutter. Press into muffin cups then brush with more butter.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Mix butter until fluffy, then add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, then your flavor, lemon juice, then add your sifted flour.
Put in your tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 50 minutes.

title: ann's baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan.
Brown onion and ground beef in bacon oil.
Crumble bacon; add all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add vegetables.
Combine milk, sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add and chill for four hours!

title: chili-rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Set aside.
Prepare yellow rice.
In large bowl, combine beef, rice and remaining ingredients except soup.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish. Pour soup on top.
Do not dilute soup.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: low sugar chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and soda.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Place in baked pie shells. Makes 2 pies.

title: chops and cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, water, parsley and green pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Brown chops.
Place on potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, sugar and margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: upside down german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Put pecans and coconut in bottom of greased pan.
Pour cake batter over nuts and coconut.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples. Heat apple juice; add flour, salt and cinnamon. Cook until thickened. Coat apple slices with juice. Fill pie crust. Dot with butter. Adjust top crust.
Sprinkle water and cinnamon over top. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 more minutes.

title: herb dressing
directions: Blend well in blender or food processor.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Saute meat and vegetables, adding one ingredient at a time. Mix pineapple juice with cornstarch and add to pan to thicken. Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: banana crunch snack
directions: Cream together the sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Add and mix in buttermilk alternately with flour.
Add and mix in rest of ingredients.
Last, fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with nuts and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: german salad
directions: Mix or cream the first 5 ingredients and fold in remaining ingredients.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese on bottom of pie crust, add sausage.
Beat eggs, in milk, add celery soup.
Add onion, hot pepper, bell pepper (anything you like) with eggs.
Pour over cheese and sausage in pie crust.
Bake at 375° until knife comes out clean.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Sautee' onion in oleo add broccoli, then steam. Add flour, mix well. Add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix together except nuts.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Put chopped nuts in bottom of pan, then add cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool to warm, then flip from pan.
Poke holes in cake with a skewer.

title: cherry fudge bars
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on package.
Stir in dry cake mix and cherries.
Pour into a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chips; layer chips, mixture, chips, mixture, etc.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs, then milk, then water. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Take off heat and add 1 stick butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Makes enough for 2 pie crusts.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Combine cornstarch and water, stirring until blended; set aside.
Combine broth and soy sauce in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Slowly pour eggs (one at a time) into rapidly boiling broth, stirring constantly.
(The egg forms lacy strands as it cooks.)
Stir cornstarch mixture into soup; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in onions. Serve immediately; about 136 calories per 1-cup serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil hens in large quantity of water with onions, pepper and celery until
chicken
is
ready to pull off bones.
Remove hens from
broth.
Bone
and
cut into bite sized pieces.
Use broth and
boil
spaghetti
until
tender.
Pour off broth and reserve. Add chicken to spaghetti.
Add tomato paste, mushroom soup
and grated
cheese.
Mix well and simmer on top of range for 25 minutes.
If it starts to get dry, add reserved broth.

title: brussels sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts in 1/2 cup water just until tender. Drain. Arrange sprouts and artichokes in buttered 1-quart casserole.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in water. Bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and simmer until tender.

title: creme puff cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Add gradually 1 cup flour. Remove from stove.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each. Cool a couple of minutes.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake in 375° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Then beat cream cheese (softened).
Add milk and vanilla pudding.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips together.
Stir in chips. Bake in floured and greased tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spanish rice pronto
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Add onion, green pepper and rice. Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add water, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Mix well.
Bring quickly to a boil. Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Blend and pour over mixture.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. When done, sprinkle with 4x sugar.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer on large tray: (first layer) bean dip or refried beans; (second layer) blended avocados with salt, pepper and lemon juice; (third layer) sour cream mixed with taco seasoning and mayonnaise; (fourth layer) minced onion; (fifth layer) drained chopped tomatoes; (sixth layer) chopped black olives and (seventh layer) shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spinach triangles (spanakopita)
directions: Combine all ingredients except filo and butter.
Mix thoroughly and taste for seasoning.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Layer bananas, wafers then pudding. Make another layer ending up with pudding mixture.
Crush a few vanilla wafers on top.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oil, add beaten eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter 5 minutes.
Add sugar slowly and eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add salt, baking powder and flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Cool 30 minutes before taking out of pan.
Grease bottom only of cake pans to allow cake to rise.

title: white chocolate cereal mix
directions: Mix the 10 cups in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate in microwave, stirring often.
Pour over cereal mix and stir until even.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: catfish court bouillon
directions: First
make
a roux (the cooking of flour and grease in equal portions,
cooked
in
large
pot).
Start
with enough grease to cover
the bottom of pot and add flour allowing the mass
to thicken
until
it
darkens
to
the color of peanut butter.
Add other
ingredients, except fish, allow to simmer for 25
minutes. Then
add

cooked fish and place lid on pot, and simmer for another 30 minutes, being sure to stir carefully from side to side in pot every once in a while to keep fish from sticking to bottom of pot or burning, and replace lid.

title: tom's fish batter
directions: Beat together egg and milk.
Dry fish fillets.
Dredge fillets in flour, then in egg and milk mixture, then in cracker crumbs. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: winter bisque
directions: Stir cream cheese and milk over medium heat in large saucepan until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally, until Velveeta is melted and soup is warmed. "Delicious on cold winter day or appetizer for holiday."

title: vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients, except dressing. Chill. Before serving, pour enough dressing over salad.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Melt butter and chocolate together. Cool. Add remaining ingredients in order given and beat well. Pour into a 9-inch buttered pie pan. Bake for 20 minutes. Cool and refrigerate. Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: Preheat 24 hours ahead.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat shortening over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Mix in brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased square baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix batter and pour over butter.
Add 3 or 4 cups of canned fruit.
Peaches are really good.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let sit one day before using. Will keep in tight container approximately 1 month in refrigerator.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Boil this together for
25 minutes; jar and seal.
Good on tacos or dip for tortilla chips.

title: alice's chicken
directions: Flatten breasts, top with Swiss cheese, roll up.
Wrap bacon around each roll.
Use toothpick to secure.
Put in baking dish. Pour wine and soy sauce over.
Top with mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast sausage and egg casserole
directions: Spread butter on both sides of bread slices; cut bread into small cubes.
Combine bread cubes, sausage, cheese, salt and pepper; stir well.
Beat eggs until foamy; stir in milk.
Add egg mixture to sausage mixture, stirring well.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually blend
in sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and salt. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour filling into crumb crust. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zha-zha-yum
directions: In a medium pot, boil 4 quarts of water.
Put in the egg noodles and 1 tsp salt; let boil until done.
Chop sirloin into small pieces; simmer until done.
Drain egg noodles.
Combine meat and the 3 cans of gravy and heat through. Add egg noodles and cook on low for a few minutes with lid on it.
Then serve.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted margarine and press into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sugar with remaining margarine and egg and pour on top of crust.
Cut bananas into long, thin slices and place on top of sugar mixture.
Add layer of pineapple and berries.
Spread top layer with whipped topping and sprinkle with pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top butter with next 5 ingredients in order
listed.
Do
not
mix
or
stir.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over all.	Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan before cutting bars.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil, stirring constantly, until a soft ball when dropped in water.
Remove from the fire. Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Drop on wax paper.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease bread pan. Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, no more, no less.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and blend in sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream, then flour and vanilla.
Mix.
Pour in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: rich and creamy chicken
directions: Spread	dried
beef
on bottom of casserole dish.
Wrap each piece
of
chicken in raw bacon strip and place on dried beef without
crowding.	Mix
soup
with
sour
cream;
spoon mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in lower oven at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Sinfully rich!

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 20 - 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove skins.
In a large skillet over medium heat, cook and stir the potatoes in butter until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.

title: cherry-coconut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Spread and flatten in ungreased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake about 25 minutes.
Stir rest of ingredients into eggs.
Spread over top of baked pastry.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars (18 bars).

title: egg rolls
directions: Put oil in pan. Add all vegetables and seasonings, cook for a few minutes until vegetables are tender. Mix in cornstarch mixture and remove from heat. In each wrapper, put some filling, seal edges, and deep fry.

title: 1-2-3 cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and mix at medium speed until blended.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in 1/2 of the chocolate chips.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool. Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: meatballs (4)
directions: Mix the onion soup mix in the hamburger.
Than add the remaining ingredients into the hamburger well.
Make the hamburger into meatballs and bake for 20-30 minutes or until done at 350°. Add meatballs to sauce and simmer 15-20 minutes.
These can be frozen.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, chicken broth, chicken soup and soup mix.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Add chicken breasts on top.
Put in oven. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter until smooth.
Gradually add sugar to the butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Continue beating, using mixer, for 4 to 5 minutes to allow plenty of time to rise properly.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour into a tube pan sprayed with Pam and sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken with prosciutto and balsamic vinegar
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sage, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour; shake off excess.
Heat olive oil in a large saute pan over medium heat.
Working in batches, brown chicken on each side, then transfer to a platter. Whisk stock into pan.
Add Prosciutto and vinegar and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; return chicken to pan and cook, basting occasionally with sauce, until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a knife, about 7 to 10 minutes.
Transfer to a warm platter.
Season sauce with salt and pepper and serve alongside.

title: bacon potato puff
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towels. In a mixing bowl, beat egg yolks until light. Beat in onion, mustard and pepper. Place potatoes in a bowl. Fold in egg mixture. Set aside 2 tablespoons bacon. Fold in cheese, parsley and remaining bacon into potatoes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together and spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Melt margarine and mix with Pepperidge Farm mix. Mix this with squash.
Reserve enough to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be mixed the day before.
Refrigerate and bake next day.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup melted butter and one egg.
Pat mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cake starts to brown a little on bottom.
Do not let cake get completely done.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Mix with mixer the yams, vanilla, coconut, 1 cup sugar, egg, milk and salt and put into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix (save out 3/4 cup dry mix), 1 egg and melt 1 stick butter.
Press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
This is the crust.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; roll in chopped pecans.
Form into a ball and refrigerate.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and start sauce.
When spaghetti is done, toss with oil in large bowl.
Reserve 1 cup spaghetti for filling. Toss remaining spaghetti with Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Turn into 10-inch pie pan.
Press spaghetti mixture into bottom and sides of pan to form crust.
Evenly spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
When sauce is done, stir in the reserved spaghetti.
Spoon meat mixture over cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover loosely with greased foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick test is good.

title: mint chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat all brownie ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x l2-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched (top may still appear wet).
Cool completely in pan.

title: pork chops and rice supreme
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops; brown in shortening.
Remove and set aside.
Pour rice into drippings in skillet; cook, stirring constantly, until light brown.
In a large casserole, place browned rice and remaining ingredients.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover; cook about 1 hour at 350°, or until liquid is absorbed.
(Easy to make and easy to eat.)

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Cream butter with sugar. Add well beaten eggs and vanilla and beat the mixture well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add the sifted ingredients to the creamed mixture. Mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a well-greased baking sheet, making sure they are spaced quite a distance apart. Place a maraschino cherry on top of each. Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: veggie oat loaf or patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into loaf or patties.
Place loaf in loaf pan and patties on cookie sheet or in muffin pan.
Bake until brown on top.
For loaf, bake for 1 hour at 350°.
For patties, bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: best biscuits
directions: Make a hole in flour and pour all ingredients in.
Mix well. Knead dough and pat on floured surface.
Cut with a biscuit cutter and bake on an ungreased sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy tarragon chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove chicken.
Blend soup, tarragon, water and wine.
Return chicken to pan.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Remove chicken to platter and keep warm.
Stir together flour and cream (or milk) and add to liquid in pan.
Simmer until thickened.
Pour about 1/2 cup over chicken.
Pass the remainder and serve with rice pilaf.

title: cauliflower and pea salad
directions: Break the cauliflower into small pieces. Add peas, cheese and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, dressing mix and sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together real good and then add flour (if it's sticking together add more flour, little bits at a time). Bake at 325 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: "southern living" homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in shortening in a large Dutch oven.
Add water, tomatoes, onion, celery, salt, pepper and brown rice.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 3 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes; stir well.
Cover and cook over medium heat an additional 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Ladle soup into individual bowls; serve warm.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Defrost broccoli enough to separate. Mix all ingredients. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites well with cream of tartar, adding white sugar as you beat.
Fold in the Ritz crackers, 3/4 cup pecans and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased pan, 8 x 8-inch tin. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with whipped cream and brown sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans on top. Refrigerate for several hours.
Cut and serve.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Slice beef in small pieces.
Mix together well.
Form into a ball.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Mix broccoli with other ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sandwich
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and stir into beef mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve on buns.
Yields 18 servings.

title: ham kabobs
directions: Cube ham and put 1 cube of ham and 1 pineapple tidbit on a toothpick.
Wrap with 1/4 piece of bacon.
Place all in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve juice from pineapple and add to 1 cup brown sugar, mustard and spices.
Mix and pour over kabobs.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 40.

title: cajun vegetable rice soup
directions: Combine broth, vegetables, tomatoes, and bay leaves in soup pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover and reduce to simmer for about 5 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add Tabasco and stir. Remove bay leaves before serving.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: In food processor or blender, blend the peppers and 1/2 the vinegar until smooth.
In 6 to 8-quart saucepan combine pepper mixture, remaining vinegar, sugar, butter or oil.
Over high heat, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in liquid pectin and return to boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring.
Fill 1/2 pint jars.
Wipe jar tops and seal with lids.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water.

title: tuna royale
directions: Cook onion and celery in small amount of water until tender. Mix soup and milk.
Add to rice with other ingredients.
Spread grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage.
Choose 8 large leaves.
Scald these in boiling water to soften and leave to drain.
Prepare the stuffings by frying onion until golden.
Add rice, stir and add 4 tablespoons water.
Bring to boil and cover.
Cook slowly until tender; 15 to 20 minutes.
Add meat and bacon, stir until browned.
Meanwhile, shred rest of cabbage finely and boil rapidly 10 minutes.
Drain and keep hot.
Place a portion of rice and meat on each cabbage leaf and roll tightly.
Tie with cotton strings or toothpick. Place rolls in baking dish.
Make a thickening from fat and flour in a frying pan; add shredded cabbage with cream.
Pour over stuffed leaves and bake in warm oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: calico potato salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Coarsely chop eggs.
Add chopped eggs to potato mixture.
Chill.
Combine remaining ingredients; toss with potato mixture 1/2 hour before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: lazy day peach cobbler
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Put butter in a very deep baking dish or pan.
Set in oven to melt.
Stir up a batter with flour, milk and sugar.
Pour this over melted butter, don't stir.
Put sugar and peaches on top, don't stir.
Bake in moderate oven one hour.
The batter will rise to the top and be brown and crisp.

title: chop chay
directions: Saute veggies in sesame oil.
Add leftover roast beef to veggies.
Add spinach.
Add clear noodles and mix.
Add about 1/3 cup soy sauce.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Separate rolls into 8 triangles. Place in bottom of pizza pan and seal. Spoon over sausage. Sprinkle with hash browns, then cheese.
Beat eggs and other ingredients except Parmesan.
Pour over pan; add Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato bacon chowder
directions: Fry bacon, until crisp, in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion and saute two to three minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add potatoes and water; bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until tender.

title: can-can chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in large casserole dish or 2 small ones.
Cook in oven at 350° for 45-60 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until very lightly golden brown.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs and molasses.
Sift flour with spices; add to sugar mixture.
Take spoonfuls and put butter on it; dip in sugar to press cookie.
Put dab of jelly in center and bake for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: dressing for spinach salad
directions: Mix in blender.
Refrigerate.
May alter salt and sugar content according to taste.

title: donut balls
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into hot fat or deep fryer (275°).
Fry until crisp, but not burned.
Roll in sugar (while still hot), powdered sugar or your own glaze.

title: simple punch(red)
directions: Mix in a gallon jug.
Finish filling jug with water.
Makes 1 gallon.
Serve cold.
Can freeze tray of punch for ice cubes.

title: german cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter on low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter with cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Blend in 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour, and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; set aside.
Beat remaining eggs until thick and light. Add remaining 3/4 cup sugar, beating until thick.
Add baking powder, salt and remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in cooled chocolate mixture, nuts, almond extract and remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Measure 1 cup batter and set aside.
Spread batter in greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Top with cheese mixture.
Drop measured 1 cup batter from a tablespoon on top and swirl with a spatula to swirl.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Cut in squares and refrigerate.
Makes 20 brownies.

title: marie's snow drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; stir until well moistened.
Spread mixture in a greased 8-inch baking pan.
Bake approximately 25 minutes or until the chocolate chips are soft.
Do not overbake!
Cut into squares and roll in confectioners sugar. Cool.
Pack in tin.
Makes 36 to 48 squares.
Keeps well!

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, garlic, chili powder, stewed tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato soup, Tabasco and sugar.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Easy!

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat 1 cup water and add apricot gelatin. Put unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix and then put mix with apricot gelatin.
Cool slightly and add sour cream and whipped topping. Stir well.
Add nuts and pour in fruit and juice.
Set in a bowl or mold.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: orange-walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 9-inch loaf pan.
Bring butter and eggs to room temperature.
In a large bowl, beat butter at medium speed until softened.
Gradually add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine flour and baking powder; gradually beat into egg mixture until just combined.
Stir in orange rind, juice, walnuts and raisins.
Stir.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Top with the remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown hamburger in dutch oven until it is brown and then drain.
Add onions, cabbage and celery.
Cook and stir until vegetable are light brown.
Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans with liquid for can, water, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat to boiling.
Turn down heat a simmer. Serve.
